                <h3>Key Topics</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li> Basic Form Structure</li>
                    <li> Input Types</li>     
                    <li>Labels & Accessibility</li>              
                    <li>Select, Textarea, Buttons</li>
                    <li>HTML5 Validation</li>
                </ul>

            <h3>In-Depth Explanation</h3>
            
            <b>a. Basic Form Structure</b> <br />

            <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0;">
                <pre>

             &lt;form action="/submit" method="POST"&gt; <br />
                 &lt;!-- Form elements go here --&gt; <br />
             &lt;/form&gt;

             </pre>
             </div>

             - FORM ATTRIBUTES: 
             <ul>
                <li> action: Where to send form data (URL) </li>
                <li>method: How to send data (GET or POST) </li>
                <li>enctype: How to encode data (important for file uploads) </li>
             </ul >

             <hr />

             <b>b. Input Types</b> <br />
                    - COMMON INPUT TYPES: <br />
                    <img src="./assets/web-dev/input-types.png" alt="table of common input types" /> <br /> 


                    - EXAMPLES: <br />

                           <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0;">
                <pre>
                    &lt;!-- Text input --&gt; 
                    &lt;label for="name">Full Name:&lt;/label&gt;  
                    &lt;input type="text" id="name" name="name"&gt;  
 
                    &lt;!-- email with placeholder--&gt; 
                    &lt;input type="email" id="email" name="email" placeholder="you@example.com"&gt;  
 
                    &lt;!-- Checkboxes--&gt; 
                    &lt;legend&gt;Select your interests:&lt;/legend&gt;  
                    &lt;input type="checkbox" id="sports" name="interest" value="sports"&gt;  
                    &lt;label for="sports">Sports:&lt;/label&gt;  
                    
                    &lt;input type="checkbox" id="music" name="interest" value="music"&gt;  
                    &lt;label for="music">Music:&lt;/label&gt;  
 
                    &lt;!-- Radio Buttons--&gt; 
                    &lt;fieldset&gt;  
                        &lt;legend&gt;Choose a size:&lt;/legend&gt;  
                        &lt;input type="radio" id="small" name="size" value="small"&gt;  
                        &lt;label for="small">Small&lt;/label&gt;  
                     
                        &lt;input type="radio" id="large" name="size" value="large"&gt;  
                        &lt;label for="large">Large&lt;/label&gt;  
                      &lt;/fieldset&gt;                      

                </pre>
                </div>
           

             <hr />

                <b>c. Labels & Accessibility</b> <br />
                    - WHY LABELS MATTER: <br />
                    1. Screen readers read the label when focus goes to input <br />
                    2. Clicking label focuses the input (better UX) <br />
                    3. Essential for accessibility compliance <br />


                    - TWO LABELING METHODS: <br />
                     <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0;">
                <pre>
                    &lt;!-- Method 1: Explicit (with for/id) --&gt;
                    &lt;label for="username">Username:&lt;/label&gt; 
                    &lt;input type="text" id="username" name="username"&gt; 

                    &lt;!-- Method 2: Implicit (wrapping) --&gt;

                    &lt;label&lt;/label&gt; 
                        Password
                        &lt;input type="password" name="password"&gt; 

                    
                    &lt;/label&gt;

                </pre>
                </div>


               <hr />

               <b>d. Select, Textarea, Buttons </b> <br />
                    - DROPDOWN (&lt;select&gt;) <br />
                     <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0;">
                        <pre>
                        
                    &lt;label for="country">Country:&lt;/label&gt;   
                    &lt;select id="country" name="country"&gt; 
                        &lt;option value=""&gt;Select a country&lt;/option&gt;  
                        &lt;option value="us"&gt;United States&lt;/option&gt;  
                        &lt;option value="ca"&gt;Canada&lt;/option&gt;  
                        &lt;option value="uk"&gt;United Kingdom&lt;/option&gt;  
                    &lt;/select&gt;
                    
                    </pre>  
                    </div>
                
                    - TEXT AREA (&lt;textarea&gt;) <br />

                     <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0;">
                        <pre>
                        
                    &lt;label for="message">Message:&lt;/label&gt;  
                    &lt;Textarea id="message" name="message" rows="4" cols="50"&gt;
                       Default Text here ...
                    &lt;/Textarea&gt;
                    
                    </pre>  
                    </div>
                <br />
                    - BUTTONS (&lt;button&gt;) <br />

                     <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0;">
                        <pre>
                        &lt;!-- Submit button --&gt;  
                    &lt;button type="submit"&gt;Send Form&lt;/button&gt;  
                    &lt;!-- Reset button --&gt;  
                    &lt;button type="reset"&gt;Clear Form&lt;/button&gt;  
                    &lt;!-- Regular button --&gt;  
                    &lt;button type="button"&gt;Click Me&lt;/button&gt;  
                    
                    </pre>  
                    </div>
            

                <hr />

                <b>e. HTML5 Validation </b> <br />

                - BUILT-IN VALIDATON ATTRIBUTES: <br />
                <img src="./assets/web-dev/built-in.png" alt="Built in form validation attributes" /> <br />

                - VALIDATION EXAMPLE: <br />
                
                <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0;">
                <pre>
                    &lt;form&gt; 
                        &lt;label for="user-email"&gt;Email:&lt;/label&gt;  
                        &lt;input type="email" id="user-email" name="email" required placeholder="example@mail.com"&gt;  

                        &lt;label for="user-password"&gt;Password:&lt;/label&gt;  
                        &lt;input type="password" id="user-password" name="password" required minlength="8"
         title="At least 8 characters"&gt;  

                        &lt;button type="submit"&gt;Register&lt;/button&gt;  
                    &lt;/form&gt; 

                </pre>
                </div>

<hr />
            <h3>Hands-On Exercise </h3>
           <b> Task:</b> Create a registration form for a school club.<br />
            <b>Requirements: </b> 

            <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0;">
                1. Form with proper action and method <br />
                2. Fields for: <br />
                   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Name (text, required) <br />
                   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Email (email type, required) <br />
                   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Password (password, minlength=8) <br />
                   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Birthdate (date type) <br />
                   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Bio (textarea, 5 rows) <br />
                   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Favorite subject (select dropdown) <br />
                   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Days available (checkboxes for Mon-Fri) <br />
                   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Experience level (radio buttons: Beginner/Intermediate/Advanced) <br />
                3. Submit and reset buttons <br />
                4. All inputs properly labeled <br />
                5. Use fieldset and legend for grouped inputs
            </div>
          
            <h3>Common Mistakes </h3>
            <p> - Missing labels: Using only placeholders (placeholders disappear when typing) <br />
            - Improper grouping: Not using fieldset/legend for related inputs <br />
            - Over-relying on HTML5 validation: Always validate on server-side too <br />
            - Inconsistent naming: name attribute should match backend expectations
</p>

                <div class="assignment-box">
                    <h4>Assignment: Weekly Project</h4>
                    <p>Create a "Contact Us" page combining everything learned this week:</p>
                    
                    <p> i. Semantic structure: <br />
                    &nbsp;- Proper DOCTYPE, charset, viewport <br />
