            "2-1": {
                icon: "fab fa-css3-alt",
                title: "CSS Foundations & Selectors",
                html: `<h1>Week 2, Day 1: Introduction to CSS & Selectors</h1>
    <p>Welcome to CSS Foundations! Today we'll learn how to make our HTML beautiful.</p>
    
    <div class="analogy-box">
        <b>Analogy: House Construction üèóÔ∏è</b><br/>
        <ul style="margin-top: 10px;">
            <li>HTML: house structure (walls, rooms, doors)</li>
            <li>CSS: int, wallpaper, furniture arrangement (how it looks)</li>
            <li>Without CSS: functioning but ugly house</li>
            <li>With CSS: beautiful, inviting home</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <h3>Key Topics</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Three Ways to Add CSS</li>
        <li>CSS Syntax - The "CSS Sentence"</li>
        <li>Basic Selectors</li>
        <li>Specificity Basics</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>In-Depth Explanation</h3>
    
    <b>a. Three Ways to Add CSS</b><br/>
    
    <b>1. Inline CSS (The "Sticky Note")</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <code>
            &lt;p style="color: red; font-size: 20px;"&gt;  This is red text&lt;/p&gt;
        </code>
        <br />
        <small>Pros: Quick for testing | Cons: Hard to maintain, can't reuse</small>
    </div>
    
    <b>2. Internal CSS (The "Notebook Page")</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            &lt;head&gt;
                &lt;style&gt;
                    p {
                        color: blue;
                        font-size: 18px;
                    }
                &lt;/style&gt;
            &lt;/head&gt;
        </pre>
        <small>Pros: Good for single-page websites | Cons: Can't share between pages</small>
    </div>
    
    <b>3. External CSS (The "Instruction Manual")</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>HTML:</b><br/>
        <pre>
            &lt;head&gt;
                &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css"&gt;
            &lt;/head&gt;
        </pre>
        <b>CSS (styles.css):</b><br/>
        <pre>
            p {
                color: green;
                font-size: 16px;
            }
        </pre>
        <small>Pros: Reusable, organized, fast loading | Cons: Extra file to manage</small>
    </div>
    
    <b>Best Practice:</b> Use <b>External CSS</b> for real projects!
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>b. CSS Syntax - The "CSS Sentence"</b><br/>
    
    <div class="analogy-box">
        <b>Analogy:</b> A CSS rule is like giving instructions:<br/>
        <ul>
            <li><b>WHO</b> should listen? (Selector)</li>
            <li><b>WHAT</b> should they do? (Property)</li>
            <li><b>HOW</b> should they do it? (Value)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /*   WHO    WHAT     HOW */
            selector  { 
                property:  value; 
            }

            /* Example: */

            p {
                 color:  blue; 
            }

            /* Translation: "All paragraphs, make your text color blue" */
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Multiple Properties:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            p {
                color: blue;             /* Property: value; */
                font-size: 18px;        /* Each on new line */
                font-family: Arial;     /* Semicolon at end! */
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Common Mistake Demo:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>WRONG - missing semicolon:</b><br/>
        <pre>
            p {
                color: blue         /* Missing semicolon! */
                font-size: 18px;     /* This won't work! */
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>c. Basic Selectors (The "WHO" in our sentence)</b><br/>
    
    <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 15px 0;">
        <tr style="background-color: #f0f0f0;">
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Selector</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Targets</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Example</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Analogy</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Element</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">All elements of that type</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>p { }</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">"All students in class"</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Class</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Elements with that class</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>.red-text { }</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">"Students with red shirts"</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>ID</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Single element with that ID</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>#main-title { }</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">"Student with ID #001"</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Universal</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">EVERY element</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>* { }</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">"Everyone in the school"</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    
    <b>HTML Setup:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            &lt;h1 id="main-title"&gt;Welcome&lt;/h1&gt;
            &lt;p class="red-text important"&gt;First paragraph&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;Second paragraph&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;p class="red-text"&gt;Third paragraph&lt;/p&gt;
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>CSS Application:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* Element selector */
            p {
                font-size: 16px;        /* Affects ALL paragraphs */
            }
            /* Class selector */
            .red-text {
                color: red;             /* Affects paragraphs 1 & 3 */
            }
            /* ID selector */
            #main-title {
                color: blue;            /* Affects ONLY the h1 */
            }
            /* Universal selector */
            * {
                margin: 0;              /* Affects EVERY element */
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>d. Specificity Basics (The "Who Wins?" Rule)</b><br/>
    
    <div class="analogy-box">
        <b>Analogy:</b> Rules in a school:<br/>
        <ol>
            <li><b>School rule</b> (Universal) = Everyone must wear shoes</li>
            <li><b>Class rule</b> (Element) = This class must wear uniforms</li>
            <li><b>Group rule</b> (Class) = Soccer team wears jerseys</li>
            <li><b>Individual rule</b> (ID) = Principal wears suit</li>
        </ol>
        <b>The more specific rule wins!</b>
    </div>
    
    <b>Specificity Hierarchy:</b><br/>
    <div style="background-color: #e0f0ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px; font-family: monospace;">
        Inline style (style="") &gt; ID &gt; Class &gt; Element &gt; Universal
    </div>
    
    <b>Example:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <code>
            &lt;p id="special" class="highlight"&gt;Text&lt;/p&gt;
        </code>
    </div>
    
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            p { color: black;  }                  /* Element: 1 point */
            .highlight { color: yellow; }       /* Class: 10 points - WINS! */
            #special { color: red; }            /* ID: 100 points - WINS! */
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Visual Specificity Calculator:</b><br/>
    <div style="background-color: #f9f9f9; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px; font-family: monospace;">
        Element: ‚ñ¢                           = 1 point<br/>
        Class:   ‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢              = 10 points<br/>
        ID:      ‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢‚ñ¢... = 100 points
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <h3>Hands-On Exercise: The Styling Challenge</h3>
    <b>Task:</b> Style a simple profile card with proper selectors<br/><br/>
    
    <b>HTML Given:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
            &lt;html&gt;
            &lt;head&gt;
                &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css"&gt;
            &lt;/head&gt;
            &lt;body&gt;
                &lt;div id="profile-card"&gt;
                    &lt;img src="avatar.jpg" alt="Avatar" class="profile-pic"&gt;
                    &lt;h1 class="name"&gt;Alex Johnson&lt;/h1&gt;
                    &lt;p class="title"&gt;Web Developer&lt;/p&gt;
                    &lt;p class="bio"&gt;I love creating beautiful websites!&lt;/p&gt;
                    &lt;div class="skills"&gt;
                        &lt;span class="skill"&gt;HTML&lt;/span&gt;
                        &lt;span class="skill"&gt;CSS&lt;/span&gt;
                        &lt;span class="skill"&gt;JavaScript&lt;/span&gt;
                    &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;/body&gt;
            &lt;/html&gt;
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Requirements for CSS:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        1. Use only <b>external CSS</b> (create style.css)<br/>
        2. Make the profile card 400px wide with a light gray background<br/>
        3. Style the name in blue using a class selector<br/>
        4. Make the title italic using a class selector<br/>
        5. Style all skills with a blue background and white text<br/>
        6. Make the bio text slightly larger than normal<br/>
        7. Add a subtle border around the entire card
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <h3>Common Mistakes & Debugging</h3>
    
    <b>Mistake 1: Selector not working</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* CSS */
            .redText { color: red; }
            <!-- HTML -->
            &lt;p class="red-text"&gt;Hello&lt;/p&gt;   /* Case sensitive! */
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Mistake 2: Forgetting to link CSS</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            &lt;!-- WRONG --&gt;
            &lt;link rel="stylesheet"&gt;           /* Missing href! */
            &lt;!-- RIGHT --&gt;
            &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css"&gt;
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Mistake 3: Path issues</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            project/
                index.html
                css/
                    styles.css  &lt;!-- Correct path: "css/styles.css" --&gt;
                                &lt;!-- Wrong path: "styles.css" --&gt;
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Debugging Tip:</b> Use Browser DevTools!<br />
    <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        1. Right-click ‚Üí Inspect Element<br/>
        2. See which styles are applied<br/>
        3. See which styles are crossed out (overridden)
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <div class="assignment-box">
        <h4>Assignment: Personal Business Card</h4>
        <p>Create a digital business card for yourself with:</p>
        
        <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
            1. External CSS file<br/>
            2. Use all four selector types at least once<br/>
            3. Include:<br/>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;- Your name (styled uniquely)<br/>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;- Your title/role<br/>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;- Contact info<br/>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;- A tagline<br/>
            4. Validate that each selector is working correctly
        </div>
        
        <p><b>Bonus:</b> Try to center your business card on the page!</p>
    </div>`
            },
            "2-2": {
                icon: "fa-brush",
                title: "Colors, Typography & Units",
                html: `<h1>Week 2, Day 2: Colors, Typography & Units</h1>
    <p>Today we'll learn how to make text beautiful and understand measurement in CSS.</p>
    
    <div class="analogy-box">
        <b>Analogy: Artist's Toolkit üé®</b><br/>
        <ul style="margin-top: 10px;">
            <li><b>Colors</b> = Your paint palette</li>
            <li><b>Typography</b> = Your handwriting style</li>
            <li><b>Units</b> = Your ruler and measuring tape</li>
            <li><b>CSS</b> = How you use all these tools together</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <h3>Key Topics</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Color Systems in CSS</li>
        <li>Typography & Web Fonts</li>
        <li>CSS Units & Measurements</li>
        <li>Color Accessibility</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>In-Depth Explanation</h3>
    
    <b>a. Color Systems in CSS</b><br/>
    
    <b>1. Named Colors (The "Crayon Box")</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            p { color: red; }
            div { background-color: lightblue; }
        </pre>
        <small>Pros: Easy to remember | Cons: Limited options (~140 colors)</small><br/>
        <small><b>Fun Fact:</b> There's actually a color called <pre>papayawhip</pre>!</small>
    </div>
    
    <b>2. Hexadecimal (The "Secret Code")</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            p { color: #ff0000; } /* Red */
            p { color: #00ff00; } /* Green */
            p { color: #0000ff; } /* Blue */
        </pre>
        <small><b>Format:</b> <pre>#RRGGBB</pre> (Red, Green, Blue)</small><br/>
        <small><b>Range:</b> 00 (none) to FF (full)</small><br/>
        <small><b>Shorthand:</b> <pre>#f00</pre> = <pre>#ff0000</pre></small><br/>
        <small><b>Memory trick:</b> <pre>#000000</pre> = black, <pre>#ffffff</pre> = white</small>
    </div>
    
    <b>3. RGB (The "Mixing Primary Colors")</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            p { color: rgb(255, 0, 0); } /* Red */
            p { color: rgb(0, 255, 0); } /* Green */
            p { color: rgb(0, 0, 255); } /* Blue */
        </pre>
        <small><b>Format:</b> <pre>rgb(red, green, blue)</pre></small><br/>
        <small><b>Range:</b> 0-255 for each color</small>
        
        <b>RGBA (with transparency):</b><br/>
        <pre>
            p { color: rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5); } /* 50% transparent red */
        </pre>
        <small>Alpha: 0 (invisible) to 1 (solid)</small>
    </div>
    
    <b>4. HSL (The "Artistic Choice")</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            p { color: hsl(0, 100%, 50%); } /* Red */
            p { color: hsl(120, 100%, 50%); } /* Green */
            p { color: hsl(240, 100%, 50%); } /* Blue */
        </pre>
        <small><b>Hue:</b> 0-360¬∞ (color wheel position)</small><br/>
        <small><b>Saturation:</b> 0-100% (intensity)</small><br/>
        <small><b>Lightness:</b> 0-100% (brightness)</small>
        
        <b>HSLA (with transparency):</b><br/>
        <pre>
            p { color: hsla(0, 100%, 50%, 0.5); }           /* 50% transparent red */
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Color Picker Demo:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            &lt;input type="color" value="#ff0000"&gt;
        </pre>
        <small>Show how changing values affects color in real-time</small>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>b. Typography - Making Text Beautiful</b><br/>
    
    <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 15px 0;">
        <tr style="background-color: #f0f0f0;">
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Property</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Controls</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Example</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Visual Effect</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>font-family</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Typeface</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>Arial, sans-serif</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Changes font style</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>font-size</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Text size</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>16px, 2em</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Bigger/smaller text</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>font-weight</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Thickness</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>bold, 700</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Light/bold text</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>font-style</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Slant</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>italic, normal</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Italic/regular</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>line-height</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Line spacing</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>1.5, 24px</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">More/less space between lines</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>letter-spacing</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Space between letters</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>2px, -1px</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Tighter/looser letters</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>text-align</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Horizontal alignment</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>center, justify</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Left/center/right</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>text-decoration</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Underlines etc.</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>underline, none</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Lines through/under text</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    
    <b>Font Stack (The "Fallback Plan"):</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            p {
                font-family: "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
            }
        </pre>
        <small>Browser tries each font until it finds one available</small>
    </div>
    
    <b>Web Fonts (Google Fonts):</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Step 1:</b> Go to <a href="https://fonts.google.com" target="_blank">fonts.google.com</a><br/>
        <b>Step 2:</b> Choose a font (e.g., "Roboto")<br/>
        <b>Step 3:</b> Add to HTML <pre>&lt;head&gt;</pre>:<br/>
        <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 10px; margin: 5px 0; border-radius: 3px;">
