                body {
                    font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
                }
            </pre>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>c. CSS Units - The "Measuring System"</b>
    
    <b>Absolute Units (Never Change):</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            px          /* pixels = One dot on screen */
            cm, mm, in  /* Real-world measurements */
            pt          /* points = For print (1pt = 1/72 inch) */
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Relative Units (Change based on something):</b>
    <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 15px 0;">
        <tr style="background-color: #f0f0f0;">
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Unit</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Relative to</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Best for</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Example</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>%</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Parent element</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Widths, heights</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>width: 50%</pre></td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>em</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Parent's font size</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Typography, spacing</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>margin: 2em</pre></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>rem</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Root (html) font size</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Consistent spacing</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>font-size: 1.5rem</pre></td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>vw</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Viewport width</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Full-width elements</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>width: 100vw</pre></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>vh</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Viewport height</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Full-height sections</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>height: 50vh</pre></td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    
    <b>The <pre>em</pre> Pitfall:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            div {
                font-size: 20px;
                padding: 2em;        /* = 40px (2 √ó 20px) */
            }
            div p {
                font-size: 0.5em;   /* = 10px (0.5 √ó 20px) */
                margin: 2em;        /* = 20px (2 √ó 10px) - NOT 40px! */
            }
            /* em compounds! */
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>The <pre>rem</pre> Solution:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            html {
                font-size: 16px;        /* Root size */
            }
            div {
                font-size: 1.25rem;     /* = 20px (1.25 √ó 16px) */
                padding: 2rem;          /* = 32px (2 √ó 16px) */
            }
            div p {
                font-size: 0.75rem;     /* = 12px (0.75 √ó 16px) */
                margin: 2rem;           /* = 32px (2 √ó 16px) - Consistent! */
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Viewport Units Demo:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            .hero {
                width: 100vw;        /* Full viewport width */
                height: 50vh;        /* Half viewport height */
                background: blue;
            }
            /* Resize browser to see it change! */
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <h3>Hands-On Exercise: Typography Poster</h3>
