    <b>Challenge Goals:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #fff0e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        - Make main-title 3√ó bigger than normal text<br/>
        - Use rem for consistent spacing<br/>
        - Create contrast with color<br/>
        - Make the quote stand out with italics and spacing
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <h3>Color Accessibility - The "Everyone Can Read" Rule</h3>
    
    <b>Contrast Ratio:</b> Text should be readable!<br/>
    <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Good:</b> Dark text on light background<br/>
        <b>Bad:</b> Light gray text on white background
    </div>
    
    <b>Quick Check:</b> Squint test<br/>
    <div style="background-color: #fff0e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        If you squint and can't read it, increase contrast!
    </div>
    
    <b>Contrast Checker Tool:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Poor contrast:</b><br/>
        <pre>
            p { 
                color: #999999; 
