            "2-3": {
                icon: "fa-box",
                title: "The Box Model",
                html: `<h1>Week 2, Day 3: The Box Model (Margin, Border, Padding).</h1>
    <p>Today we'll master spacing, element sizing, and how elements behave on the page.</p>
    
    <div class="analogy-box">
        <b>Analogy: Gift Boxes in a Shipping Warehouse üéÅ</b><br/>
        <ul style="margin-top: 10px;">
            <li><b>Content</b> = The actual gift inside</li>
            <li><b>Padding</b> = Bubble wrap around the gift</li>
            <li><b>Border</b> = The gift box itself</li>
            <li><b>Margin</b> = Space between boxes on the shelf</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <h3>Key Topics</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>The Four Layers of the Box Model</li>
        <li>The Box-Sizing Revolution</li>
        <li>Display Property - How Elements Behave</li>
        <li>Margin Collapse - The "Space Merging" Quirk</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>In-Depth Explanation</h3>
    
    <b>a. The Four Layers of the Box Model</b><br/>
    
    <div style="background-color: #f9f9f9; padding: 20px; margin: 15px 0; border: 2px dashed #ccc; text-align: center;">
        <div style="background-color: #ffcccc; padding: 30px; margin: 20px; border: 5px solid #ff6666; display: inline-block; position: relative;">
            <div style="background-color: #ccffcc; padding: 20px; border: 3px solid #66cc66;">
                <div style="background-color: #cce6ff; padding: 10px; border: 2px solid #3399ff;">
                    <strong>Content Area</strong>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div style="position: absolute; top: -25px; left: 10px; color: #ff6666; font-weight: bold;">Margin</div>
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 10px; left: -35px; color: #ff6666; font-weight: bold;">‚Üê Margin</div>
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 10px; right: -35px; color: #ff6666; font-weight: bold;">Margin ‚Üí</div>
            <div style="position: absolute; bottom: -25px; left: 10px; color: #ff6666; font-weight: bold;">Margin</div>
            
            <div style="position: absolute; top: -5px; left: 20px; color: #66cc66; font-weight: bold;">Border</div>
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 20px; left: -15px; color: #66cc66; font-weight: bold;">‚Üê Border</div>
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 20px; right: -15px; color: #66cc66; font-weight: bold;">Border ‚Üí</div>
            <div style="position: absolute; bottom: -5px; left: 20px; color: #66cc66; font-weight: bold;">Border</div>
            
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 15px; left: 30px; color: #3399ff; font-weight: bold;">Padding</div>
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 30px; left: 5px; color: #3399ff; font-weight: bold;">‚Üê Padding</div>
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 30px; right: 5px; color: #3399ff; font-weight: bold;">Padding ‚Üí</div>
            <div style="position: absolute; bottom: 15px; left: 30px; color: #3399ff; font-weight: bold;">Padding</div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <b>1. Content - The "Actual Stuff"</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            div {
                width: 200px;   /* Content width */
                height: 100px;  /* Content height */
            }
        </pre>
        <small>The actual text, image, or element content</small><br/>
        <small>Controlled by <pre>width</pre> and <pre>height</pre> properties</small>
    </div>
    
    <b>2. Padding - The "Cushion Zone"</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            div {
                padding: 20px;                  /* All sides */
                padding: 10px 20px;             /* Top/Bottom, Left/Right */
                padding: 10px 20px 30px 40px;   /* Top, Right, Bottom, Left */
            }
        </pre>
        <small>Space <b>inside</b> the element, around content</small><br/>
        <small><b>Memory trick:</b> Padding = Inside space (like pillow padding)</small>
    </div>
    
    <b>3. Border - The "Wrapper"</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            div {
                border: 3px solid black;            /* Shorthand */
                border-width: 3px;                  /* Separate properties */
                border-style: solid;
                border-color: black;
                border-radius: 10px;                /* Rounded corners! */
            }
        </pre>
        <small>The visible edge of the element</small><br/>
        <small>Styles: <code>solid</code>, <code>dotted</code>, <code>dashed</code>, <code>double</code>, <code>groove</code>, <code>ridge</code></small>
    </div>
    
    <b>4. Margin - The "Personal Space"</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            div {
                margin: 20px;                           /* Same syntax as padding */
                margin-top: 10px;
                margin: 0 auto;                         /* Center horizontally */
            }
        </pre>
        <small>Space <b>outside</b> the element, between elements</small><br/>
        <small><b>Memory trick:</b> Margin = Outside space (like personal margin)</small>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>b. The Box-Sizing Revolution</b><br/>
    
    <b>Problem:</b> The old way (content-box)
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            div {
                width: 200px;
                padding: 20px;
                border: 5px solid black;
                /* Actual width = 200 + 20 + 20 + 5 + 5 = 250px! */
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Solution:</b> <pre>box-sizing: border-box</pre>
    <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            div {
                box-sizing: border-box;
                width: 200px;
                padding: 20px;
                border: 5px solid black;
                /* Width stays 200px total! Padding/border INSIDE */
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <div class="analogy-box">
        <b>Analogy:</b><br/>
        - <pre>content-box</pre> = Buying a 200cm shelf, then adding wrapping ‚Üí Takes more space<br/>
        - <pre>border-box</pre> = 200cm TOTAL including wrapping ‚Üí Predictable size
    </div>
    
    <b>The Modern Standard:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            * {
                box-sizing: border-box;     /* Apply to everything! */
            }
                                            /* Or reset with: */
            html {
                box-sizing: border-box;
            }
            *, *:before, *:after {
                box-sizing: inherit;
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>c. Display Property - How Elements Behave</b><br/>
    
    <b>Three Main Types:</b>
    <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 15px 0;">
        <tr style="background-color: #f0f0f0;">
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Type</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Behavior</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Example Elements</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Can set width/height?</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Block</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Takes full width, new line</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>div</pre>, <pre>p</pre>, <pre>h1-h6</pre>, <pre>section</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd; text-align: center;">‚úÖ Yes</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Inline</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Flows with text, only content width</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>span</pre>, <pre>a</pre>, <pre>strong</pre>, <pre>em</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd; text-align: center;">‚ùå No</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Inline-block</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Flows like inline, but respects dimensions</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>img</pre>, <pre>button</pre>, <pre>input</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd; text-align: center;">‚úÖ Yes</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    
    <b>Visual Comparison:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #f9f9f9; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <div style="background-color: lightblue; padding: 10px; margin: 5px 0;">Block 1</div>
        <div style="background-color: lightgreen; padding: 10px; margin: 5px 0;">Block 2</div>
        
        <span style="background-color: yellow; padding: 10px;">Inline 1</span>
        <span style="background-color: orange; padding: 10px;">Inline 2</span>
        <br/><br/>
        
        <div style="display: inline-block; background-color: pink; width: 100px; padding: 10px;">Inline-block 1</div>
        <div style="display: inline-block; background-color: lavender; width: 100px; padding: 10px;">Inline-block 2</div>
    </div>
    
    <b>Changing Display:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* Make inline element behave like block */
            a {
                display: block;
                width: 200px;
            }
            /* Make block element flow inline */
