    </div>
    
    <div style="background-color: #f9f9f9; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <div style="margin-bottom: 50px; background: #ffcccc; padding: 15px;">Top (margin-bottom: 50px)</div>
        <div style="margin-top: 30px; background: #ccccff; padding: 15px;">Bottom (margin-top: 30px)</div>
        <small>Only 50px gap, not 80px!</small>
    </div>
    
    <b>When margins DON'T collapse:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        1. Horizontal margins (left/right) never collapse<br/>
        2. With padding or border between elements<br/>
        3. With <code>display: flex</code> or <code>display: grid</code> parents
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <h3>Hands-On Exercise: The Box Model Builder</h3>
    <b>Interactive Activity:</b> Build a visual box model calculator<br/><br/>
    
    <b>HTML Setup:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            &lt;div class="box-model-demo"&gt;
                &lt;div class="content"&gt;Content Area&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div class="controls"&gt;
