    <hr/>
    
    <h3>Common Layout Problems & Solutions</h3>
    
    <b>Problem 1: Elements too wide with padding</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* Old way: Calculate manually */
            div {
                width: 400px;
                padding: 20px;
                /* Actually 440px wide! */
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* Solution: Use border-box */
            div {
                box-sizing: border-box;
                width: 400px;
                padding: 20px;
                /* Stays 400px! */
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Problem 2: Centering block elements</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* Old way: Calculate margins */
            div {
                width: 300px;
                margin-left: calc(50% - 150px); /* Complex! */
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* Solution: auto margins */
            div {
                width: 300px;
                margin: 0 auto; /* Centers horizontally! */
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Problem 3: Inline elements ignoring dimensions</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
