            - Centered copyright text<br/>
            - Different background color<br/><br/>
            
            <b>Technical Requirements:</b><br/>
            1. Use external CSS with proper selectors<br/>
            2. Use rem units for font sizes<br/>
            3. Use em units for padding/margins<br/>
            4. Use hex, rgb, and hsl colors<br/>
            5. Validate your HTML and CSS
        </div>
        
        <p><b>Bonus Challenge:</b> Add a "Back to top" button that appears after scrolling and uses fixed positioning.</p>
    </div>`
            },

            "3-1": {
                "icon": "fa-boxes-stacked",
                "title": "Flexbox Containers & Alignment",
                "html": "<h1>Week 3, Day 1: Flexbox Containers & Alignment.</h1>\n<p>Master one-dimensional layouts with CSS Flexbox, from fundamentals to advanced real-world patterns.</p>\n\n<div class=\"analogy-box\">\n    <b>Core Analogy: Train Cars on a Track üöÇ</b><br/>\n    <ul style=\"margin-top: 10px;\">\n        <li><b>Flex Container</b> = The train track</li>\n        <li><b>Flex Items</b> = Individual train cars</li>\n        <li><b>Main Axis</b> = Direction the train moves</li>\n        <li><b>Cross Axis</b> = Perpendicular direction</li>\n        <li><b>Flex Properties</b> = How cars arrange on the track</li>\n    </ul>\n</div>\n\n<h3>Key Topics</h3>\n<ul>\n    <li>Flex Container vs Flex Items</li>\n    <li>Main Axis vs Cross Axis</li>\n    <li>Justify Content & Align Items</li>\n    <li>Flex Grow, Shrink, & Basis</li>\n    <li>Ordering & Flex Wrap</li>\n    <li>Responsive Layout Patterns</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>In-Depth Explanation</h3>\n\n<b>1. Core Concepts</b><br/>\n\n<b>Basic Flex Setup:</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        /* CSS */<br/>\n        .flex-container {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: flex;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Turns container into flex container */<br/>\n        }<br/>\n        /* All direct children become flex items */\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<b>Visual Example:</b>\n<div style=\"display: flex; background-color: #f0f0f0; padding: 20px; margin: 15px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <div style=\"background-color: lightblue; padding: 20px; margin: 5px; flex: 1;\">Item 1</div>\n    <div style=\"background-color: lightgreen; padding: 20px; margin: 5px; flex: 1;\">Item 2</div>\n    <div style=\"background-color: lightcoral; padding: 20px; margin: 5px; flex: 1;\">Item 3</div>\n</div>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<b>2. Axes & Direction</b><br/>\n\n<div style=\"display: flex; justify-content: space-between; margin: 15px 0;\">\n    <div style=\"text-align: center; padding: 15px; background-color: #e8f5e8; border-radius: 5px; flex: 1; margin-right: 10px;\">\n        <h4>Main Axis</h4>\n        <div style=\"width: 100%; height: 4px; background-color: #4CAF50; margin: 10px 0;\"></div>\n        <small>Primary direction (row or column)</small><br/>\n        <pre>flex-direction: row;</pre>\n    </div>\n    <div style=\"text-align: center; padding: 15px; background-color: #e8f5e8; border-radius: 5px; flex: 1; margin-left: 10px;\">\n        <h4>Cross Axis</h4>\n        <div style=\"width: 4px; height: 80px; background-color: #2196F3; margin: 10px auto;\"></div>\n        <small>Perpendicular direction</small><br/>\n        <pre>align-items: stretch;</pre>\n    </div>\n</div>\n\n<b>Changing Direction:</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        .flex-container {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: flex;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;flex-direction: row;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Default (‚Üí) */<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;flex-direction: column;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* (‚Üì) */<br/>\n        }\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<b>3. Alignment Properties</b><br/>\n\n<b>justify-content (Main Axis):</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        .flex-container {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: flex;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;justify-content: flex-start;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Items at start */<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;justify-content: center;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Items centered */<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;justify-content: space-between;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Equal space between */<br/>\n        }\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<b>align-items (Cross Axis):</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        .flex-container {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: flex;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;align-items: flex-start;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Align to top */<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;align-items: center;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Center vertically */<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;align-items: stretch;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Default - fill container */<br/>\n        }\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<b>4. Flex Items Properties</b><br/>\n\n<b>The Flex Shorthand:</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        .item {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;flex: grow shrink basis;<br/>\n        }<br/><br/>\n        /* Examples: */<br/>\n        .item { flex: 1; }&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* flex: 1 1 0 */<br/>\n        .item { flex: 0 1 auto; }&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Don't grow, can shrink, auto basis */<br/>\n        .item { flex: 0 0 250px; }&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Fixed width sidebar */\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<b>Flex Grow Example:</b>\n<div style=\"display: flex; background-color: #f0f0f0; padding: 10px; margin: 15px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <div style=\"background-color: lightblue; padding: 20px; margin: 5px; flex-grow: 1;\">flex-grow: 1</div>\n    <div style=\"background-color: lightgreen; padding: 20px; margin: 5px; flex-grow: 2;\">flex-grow: 2 (2√ó more)</div>\n    <div style=\"background-color: lightcoral; padding: 20px; margin: 5px; flex-grow: 1;\">flex-grow: 1</div>\n</div>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<b>5. Advanced Techniques</b><br/>\n\n<b>Ordering Items:</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        .item-1 { order: 3; }&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Appears third */<br/>\n        .item-2 { order: 1; }&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Appears first */<br/>\n        .item-3 { order: 2; }&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Appears second */\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<b>Flex Wrap (Responsive Layouts):</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        .container {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: flex;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;flex-wrap: wrap;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Allows items to wrap */<br/>\n        }<br/>\n        .item {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;flex: 1 1 300px;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Grow, shrink, basis 300px */<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;min-width: 250px;<br/>\n        }\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<b>Perfect Centering:</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        .centered-container {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: flex;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;justify-content: center;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;align-items: center;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;height: 100vh;<br/>\n        }\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<h3>Real-World Patterns</h3>\n\n<b>1. Responsive Navigation Bar</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        /* Mobile: vertical stack */<br/>\n        .nav {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: flex;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;flex-direction: column;<br/>\n        }<br/><br/>\n        /* Desktop: horizontal row */<br/>\n        @media (min-width: 768px) {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;.nav {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;flex-direction: row;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;justify-content: space-between;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;}<br/>\n        }\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<b>2. Holy Grail Layout</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        .container {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: flex;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;min-height: 100vh;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;flex-direction: column;<br/>\n        }<br/><br/>\n        .main {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: flex;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;flex: 1;<br/>\n        }<br/><br/>\n        .sidebar { flex: 0 0 250px; }<br/>\n        .content { flex: 1; }\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<h3>Common Flexbox Mistakes</h3>\n\n<b>Mistake 1: Forgetting display: flex</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        /* WRONG - flex properties won't work */<br/>\n        .container {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;justify-content: center;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Does nothing! */<br/>\n        }<br/><br/>\n        /* RIGHT */<br/>\n        .container {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: flex;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;justify-content: center;<br/>\n        }\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<b>Mistake 2: Confusing axes with flex-direction</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        /* When flex-direction is column: */<br/>\n        .container {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: flex;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;flex-direction: column;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;justify-content: center;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Works on VERTICAL axis now */<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;/* Use align-items for horizontal center in column */<br/>\n        }\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<div class=\"assignment-box\">\n    <h4>Comprehensive Assignment: Dashboard Layout</h4>\n    <p>Build a complete, responsive dashboard using flexbox:</p>\n    \n    <div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n        <b>Requirements:</b><br/>\n        1. Fixed sidebar (250px) + main content area<br/>\n        2. Responsive header with navigation<br/>\n        3. Dashboard card grid (3√ó2 on desktop)<br/>\n        4. Mobile: sidebar becomes hamburger menu<br/>\n        5. Use flex-wrap for responsive card grid<br/>\n        6. Implement proper flex-grow/shrink behavior<br/><br/>\n        \n        <b>Technical Skills Demonstrated:</b><br/>\n        ‚Ä¢ Nested flex containers<br/>\n        ‚Ä¢ Responsive patterns with media queries<br/>\n        ‚Ä¢ Flex item ordering for mobile-first<br/>\n        ‚Ä¢ Equal height columns<br/>\n        ‚Ä¢ Perfect centering techniques\n    </div>\n    \n    <p><b>Bonus Challenge:</b> Add a dark/light mode toggle using flexbox for alignment.</p>\n</div>"

            },
            "3-2": {
                "icon": "fa-grip",
                "title": "CSS Grid Mastery & Layout Strategies",
                "html": "<h1>Week 3, Day 2: CSS Grid Mastery & Layout Strategies</h1>\n<p>Master two-dimensional layouts with CSS Grid and learn when to combine with Flexbox for optimal results.</p>\n\n<div class=\"analogy-box\">\n    <b>Core Analogy: City Planning üèôÔ∏è</b><br/>\n    <ul style=\"margin-top: 10px;\">\n        <li><b>Grid Template</b> = City block layout</li>\n        <li><b>Grid Items</b> = Buildings</li>\n        <li><b>Grid Lines</b> = Streets</li>\n        <li><b>Auto-fit/auto-fill</b> = Automatic neighborhood planning</li>\n        <li><b>Grid + Flexbox</b> = City planning + interior design</li>\n    </ul>\n</div>\n\n<h3>Key Topics</h3>\n<ul>\n    <li>Grid Container vs Grid Items</li>\n    <li>Grid Template Columns/Rows & fr Units</li>\n    <li>Auto-fit, Auto-fill & Minmax()</li>\n    <li>Grid Lines, Areas & Alignment</li>\n    <li>Grid vs Flexbox Decision Making</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>In-Depth Explanation</h3>\n\n<b>1. Core Grid Setup</b><br/>\n\n<b>Basic Grid Structure:</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        .grid-container {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: grid;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Turns container into grid */<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* 2 equal columns */<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-template-rows: 100px 100px;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* 2 rows */<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;gap: 20px;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Spacing between items */<br/>\n        }\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<b>Visual Grid Example:</b>\n<div style=\"display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; grid-template-rows: 100px 100px; gap: 10px; background-color: #f0f0f0; padding: 20px; margin: 15px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <div style=\"background-color: lightblue; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: bold;\">A</div>\n    <div style=\"background-color: lightgreen; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: bold;\">B</div>\n    <div style=\"background-color: lightcoral; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: bold;\">C</div>\n    <div style=\"background-color: lavender; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: bold;\">D</div>\n</div>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<b>2. Grid Units & Templates</b><br/>\n\n<b>The fr Unit (Fractional):</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <b>Example:</b> <pre>grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr 1fr</pre><br/>\n    <b>Calculation:</b> Total fractions = 1 + 2 + 1 = 4<br/>\n    <b>Column 1:</b> 1/4 = 25% of available space<br/>\n    <b>Column 2:</b> 2/4 = 50% of available space<br/>\n    <b>Column 3:</b> 1/4 = 25% of available space\n</div>\n\n<b>Grid Template Patterns:</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        /* 3 equal columns */<br/>\n        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);<br/><br/>\n        /* Fixed sidebar, flexible content */<br/>\n        grid-template-columns: 250px 1fr;<br/><br/>\n        /* Mixed units */<br/>\n        grid-template-columns: 100px auto 1fr 2fr;\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<b>3. Responsive Grids: Auto-fit vs Auto-fill</b><br/>\n\n<b>Auto-fill:</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr));</pre><br/>\n    <small>- Creates tracks for ALL possible items</small><br/>\n    <small>- Empty tracks remain (take up space)</small>\n</div>\n\n<b>Auto-fit:</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));</pre><br/>\n    <small>- Creates tracks only for EXISTING items</small><br/>\n    <small>- Collapses empty tracks</small>\n</div>\n\n<b>Minmax() Function:</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        /* Syntax: minmax(minimum, maximum) */<br/>\n        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));<br/>\n        /* Items: minimum 250px, maximum 1 fraction */\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<b>4. Grid Lines & Areas</b><br/>\n\n<b>Positioning with Grid Lines:</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        .item {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-column: 1 / 3;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Start at line 1, end at line 3 */<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-row: 1 / 2;<br/>\n        }<br/><br/>\n        /* Shorthand: */<br/>\n        .item {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-area: 1 / 1 / 2 / 3;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* row-start / column-start / row-end / column-end */<br/>\n        }\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<b>Named Grid Areas (Clean Structure):</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        .container {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: grid;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-template-areas:<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\"header header header\"<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\"sidebar content content\"<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\"footer footer footer\";<br/>\n        }<br/><br/>\n        .header { grid-area: header; }<br/>\n        .sidebar { grid-area: sidebar; }\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<b>5. Grid Alignment</b><br/>\n\n<b>Alignment Properties:</b>\n<div style=\"display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin: 15px 0;\">\n    <div style=\"background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;\">\n        <h4>Justify-* (Inline Axis)</h4>\n        <pre>justify-items</pre> - Items in cells<br/>\n        <pre>justify-content</pre> - Grid in container<br/>\n        <pre>justify-self</pre> - Single item\n    </div>\n    <div style=\"background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;\">\n        <h4>Align-* (Block Axis)</h4>\n        <pre>align-items</pre> - Items in cells<br/>\n        <pre>align-content</pre> - Grid in container<br/>\n        <pre>align-self</pre> - Single item\n    </div>\n</div>\n\n<b>Perfect Centering:</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        .container {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: grid;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;place-items: center;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Short for align-items + justify-items */<br/>\n        }\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<b>6. Grid vs Flexbox: When to Use Which</b><br/>\n\n<b>The Decision Matrix:</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #f9f9f9; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <b>Use CSS Grid when:</b><br/>\n    ‚úÖ Need 2D layout (rows AND columns)<br/>\n    ‚úÖ Precise control over both axes<br/>\n    ‚úÖ Creating complete page layouts<br/>\n    ‚úÖ Want gap property<br/><br/>\n    \n    <b>Use Flexbox when:</b><br/>\n    ‚úÖ Need 1D layout (row OR column)<br/>\n    ‚úÖ Content distribution along one axis<br/>\n    ‚úÖ Dynamic wrapping of items<br/>\n    ‚úÖ Building navigation bars, card lists\n</div>\n\n<b>Combine Both for Best Results:</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        /* Grid for overall page layout */<br/>\n        .page {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: grid;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-template-areas: \"header\" \"main\" \"footer\";<br/>\n        }<br/><br/>\n        /* Flexbox for items inside grid cells */<br/>\n        .nav {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: flex;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;justify-content: space-between;<br/>\n        }<br/><br/>\n        .card-grid {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: grid;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Grid for arrangement */<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));<br/>\n        }<br/><br/>\n        .card {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: flex;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Flexbox for content */<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;flex-direction: column;<br/>\n        }\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<b>7. Creative Overlap & Advanced Features</b><br/>\n\n<b>Intentional Overlap:</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        .item1 {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-column: 1 / 3;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;z-index: 1;<br/>\n        }<br/>\n        .item2 {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-column: 2;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-row: 1 / 3;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;z-index: 2;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Appears above */<br/>\n        }\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<b>Overlap Example:</b>\n<div style=\"display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; grid-template-rows: 150px 150px; gap: 10px; background-color: #f0f0f0; padding: 20px; margin: 15px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <div style=\"background-color: rgba(173, 216, 230, 0.8); grid-column: 1 / 3; grid-row: 1; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;\">Item 1 (spans 2 columns)</div>\n    <div style=\"background-color: rgba(144, 238, 144, 0.8); grid-column: 2; grid-row: 1 / 3; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;\">Item 2 (spans 2 rows)</div>\n    <div style=\"background-color: rgba(240, 128, 128, 0.8); grid-column: 1; grid-row: 2; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;\">Item 3</div>\n</div>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<h3>Common Grid Mistakes</h3>\n\n<b>Mistake 1: Forgetting display: grid</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        /* WRONG - grid properties won't work */<br/>\n        .container {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Does nothing! */<br/>\n        }<br/><br/>\n        /* RIGHT */<br/>\n        .container {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: grid;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;<br/>\n        }\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<b>Mistake 2: Confusing fr with %</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        /* WRONG - 100% + 1fr causes overflow */<br/>\n        grid-template-columns: 100% 1fr;<br/><br/>\n        /* BETTER */<br/>\n        grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* 33% / 66% */<br/>\n        grid-template-columns: 250px 1fr;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Fixed + flexible */\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<h3>Real-World Patterns</h3>\n\n<b>Pattern 1: Dashboard Layout</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        .dashboard {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: grid;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-template-areas:<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\"header header header\"<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\"sidebar main widgets\"<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\"footer footer footer\";<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-template-columns: 250px 1fr 300px;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-template-rows: auto 1fr auto;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;min-height: 100vh;<br/>\n        }\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<b>Pattern 2: Responsive Photo Gallery</b>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <pre>\n        .gallery {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;display: grid;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;gap: 20px;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-auto-flow: dense;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Fill gaps */<br/>\n        }<br/>\n        .featured {<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-column: span 2;<br/>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;grid-row: span 2;<br/>\n        }\n    </pre>\n</div>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<div class=\"assignment-box\">\n    <h4>Comprehensive Assignment: News Portal Website</h4>\n    <p>Build a complete news portal combining Grid and Flexbox:</p>\n    \n    <div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;\">\n        <b>Layout Requirements:</b><br/>\n        1. Use Grid for overall page structure<br/>\n        2. Use Flexbox for navigation and component interiors<br/>\n        3. Implement 3 responsive breakpoints<br/>\n        4. Include overlapping hero section<br/>\n        5. Create responsive article grid with auto-fit<br/><br/>\n        \n        <b>Sections to Build:</b><br/>\n        ‚Ä¢ Sticky header (Flexbox navigation)<br/>\n        ‚Ä¢ Hero with overlapping text (Grid)<br/>\n        ‚Ä¢ Featured articles (Grid with auto-fit)<br/>\n        ‚Ä¢ Sidebar widgets (Grid sub-layout)<br/>\n        ‚Ä¢ Footer with columns (Grid)<br/><br/>\n        \n        <b>Technical Skills:</b><br/>\n        ‚Ä¢ grid-template-areas for clarity<br/>\n        ‚Ä¢ minmax() for responsive sizing<br/>\n        ‚Ä¢ Appropriate Grid/Flexbox combination<br/>\n        ‚Ä¢ Gap property for consistent spacing\n    </div>\n    \n    <p><b>Bonus Challenge:</b> Implement a dark/light mode toggle that switches grid layouts.</p>\n</div>"
            },
            "3-3": {
                icon: "fa-tablet",
                title: "Responsive Design: Media Queries.",
                html: `<h1>Week 3, Day 3: Responsive Design Principles: Media Queries.</h1>
    <p>Today we'll learn how to make websites work beautifully on all devices - from phones to desktops.</p>
    
    <div class="analogy-box">
        <b>Analogy: Water vs Rock üíß</b><br/>
        <ul style="margin-top: 10px;">
            <li><b>Fluid Layouts</b> = Water that fills any container</li>
            <li><b>Fixed Layouts</b> = Rock that stays the same shape</li>
            <li><b>Breakpoints</b> = Points where water changes state (ice ‚Üî water ‚Üî steam)</li>
            <li><b>Responsive Design</b> = Being like water - adapting to any container</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <h3>Key Topics</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Mobile-First vs Desktop-First Approach</li>
        <li>Media Queries & Breakpoints</li>
        <li>Responsive Typography & Spacing</li>
        <li>Viewport Units & Fluid Layouts</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>In-Depth Explanation</h3>
    
    <b>a. Mobile-First vs Desktop-First</b><br/>
    
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin: 15px 0;">
        <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
            <h4>Mobile-First Approach</h4>
            <small><b>Strategy:</b> Start small, then enhance</small><br/>
            <small><b>CSS:</b> Base styles for mobile, media queries for larger screens</small><br/>
            <small><b>Media Queries:</b> <pre>min-width</pre></small><br/>
            <small><b>Philosophy:</b> Progressive enhancement</small><br/><br/>
            <pre>
                /* Mobile styles (default) */
                .container { padding: 1rem; }
                /* Tablet */
                @media (min-width: 768px) {
                    .container { padding: 2rem; }
                }
                /* Desktop */
                @media (min-width: 1024px) {
                    .container { padding: 3rem; }
                }
            </pre>
        </div>
        <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
            <h4>Desktop-First Approach</h4>
            <small><b>Strategy:</b> Start large, then adapt down</small><br/>
            <small><b>CSS:</b> Base styles for desktop, media queries for smaller screens</small><br/>
            <small><b>Media Queries:</b> <pre>max-width</pre></small><br/>
            <small><b>Philosophy:</b> Graceful degradation</small><br/><br/>
            <pre>
                /* Desktop styles (default) */
                .container { padding: 3rem; }
                /* Tablet */
                @media (max-width: 1023px) {
                    .container { padding: 2rem; }
                }
                /* Mobile */
                @media (max-width: 767px) {
                    .container { padding: 1rem; }
                }
            </pre>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <b>Which to Choose?</b>
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Mobile-First is Recommended Because:</b><br/>
        1. <b>Performance:</b> Mobile gets minimal CSS<br/>
        2. <b>Growth:</b> Easier to add features than remove them<br/>
        3. <b>Mobile Traffic:</b> Most web traffic is now mobile<br/>
        4. <b>Future-Proof:</b> Works better with new devices<br/>
        5. <b>Google:</b> Mobile-first indexing (SEO benefit)
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>b. Media Queries - The "Conditional CSS"</b><br/>
    
    <b>Basic Media Query Structure:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            @media media-type and (media-feature) { 
                /* CSS rules here */    
            }     
            /* Example: */  
            @media screen and (min-width: 768px) {  
                .container {    
                    max-width: 1200px;  
                }   
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Common Media Features:</b>
    <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 15px 0;">
        <tr style="background-color: #f0f0f0;">
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Feature</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">What it Checks</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Example</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Use Case</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>width</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Viewport width</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>(min-width: 768px)</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Tablet and up</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>height</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Viewport height</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>(max-height: 600px)</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Short screens</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>orientation</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Portrait or landscape</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>(orientation: landscape)</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Tablets rotated</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>aspect-ratio</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Width to height ratio</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>(aspect-ratio: 16/9)</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Widescreen devices</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>resolution</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Pixel density</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>(min-resolution: 2dppx)</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Retina displays</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>hover</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Hover capability</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>(hover: hover)</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Desktop with mouse</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>prefers-color-scheme</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Dark/light mode</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>(prefers-color-scheme: dark)</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Dark mode users</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>prefers-reduced-motion</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Motion sensitivity</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><pre>(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)</pre></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Accessibility</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    
    <b>Common Breakpoints (Mobile-First):</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* Small phones: < 576px (no media query needed - mobile-first!) */ 
            /* Base styles work for all mobile */     
            /* Small tablets and large phones */    
            @media (min-width: 576px) { 
                /* CSS for ‚â•576px */    
            }     
            /* Tablets */   
            @media (min-width: 768px) { 
                /* CSS for ‚â•768px */    
            }     
            /* Small desktops */    
            @media (min-width: 992px) { 
                /* CSS for ‚â•992px */    
            }     
            /* Large desktops */    
            @media (min-width: 1200px) {    
                /* CSS for ‚â•1200px */   
            }     
            /* Extra large */   
            @media (min-width: 1400px) {    
                /* CSS for ‚â•1400px */   
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Logical Operators (and, or, not):</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* AND - both conditions must be true */    
            @media screen and (min-width: 768px) and (max-width: 1023px) {  
                /* Tablet only */   
            }     
            /* OR - use comma to separate queries */    
            @media (min-width: 1200px), (orientation: landscape) {  
                /* Large screens OR landscape */    
            }     
            /* NOT - invert the condition */    
            @media not screen and (color) { 
                /* Not a color screen */    
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>c. Responsive Typography & Spacing</b><br/>
    
    <b>The Problem with Fixed Units:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* WRONG - looks tiny on mobile, huge on desktop */ 
            h1 {    
                font-size: 48px;    /* Too big for mobile! */   
            }   
            p { 
                font-size: 16px;    /* Too small for desktop! */    
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Solution 1: Media Queries for Typography</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* Mobile-first typography */   
            h1 {    
                font-size: 2rem;    /* 32px if root is 16px */  
            }     
            @media (min-width: 768px) { 
                h1 {    
                    font-size: 2.5rem;  /* 40px */  
                }   
            }     
            @media (min-width: 1200px) {    
                h1 {    
                    font-size: 3rem;    /* 48px */  
                }   
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Solution 2: Fluid Typography with calc()</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* Fluid typography - scales smoothly */    
            h1 {    
                font-size: calc(1.5rem + 2vw);  /* Scales with viewport */    
                /* At 320px: ~1.5rem + 6.4px = ~30.4px */   
                /* At 1200px: ~1.5rem + 24px = ~48px */ 
            }     
            /* Even better with clamp() */  
            h1 {    
                font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 3rem);    
                /* Minimum: 1.5rem (24px) */    
                /* Preferred: 4vw (scales with viewport) */ 
                /* Maximum: 3rem (48px) */  
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Responsive Spacing:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* Base spacing for mobile */   
            .container {    
                padding: 1rem;  
                margin-bottom: 1.5rem;  
            }     
            /* Increase spacing on larger screens */    
            @media (min-width: 768px) { 
                .container {    
                    padding: 2rem;  
                    margin-bottom: 3rem;    
                }   
            }     
            /* Fluid spacing with viewport units */ 
            .hero { 
                padding: 5vh 5vw;   /* Scales with viewport size */    
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>d. Viewport Units & Fluid Layouts</b><br/>
    
    <b>Viewport Units Recap:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
            vw   - 1% of viewport width<br/>
            vh   - 1% of viewport height<br/>
            vmin     - 1% of viewport's smaller dimension<br/>
            vmax     - 1% of viewport's larger dimension
    </div>
    
    <b>Fluid Layout Examples:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* Full viewport hero section */    
            .hero { 
                width: 100vw;                        /* Full width */   
                height: 100vh;                       /* Full height */ 
                padding: 5vh 5vw;                    /* Proportional padding */ 
            }     
            /* Fluid container with max-width */    
            .container {    
                width: 90vw;                          /* 90% of viewport */ 
                max-width: 1200px;                   /* But never more than 1200px */  
                margin: 0 auto;                      /* Center it */  
            }     
            /* Responsive font with vw */   
            h1 {    
                font-size: calc(24px + 2vw);        /* Scales with width */ 
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>The Problem with 100vh on Mobile:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* PROBLEM - includes browser UI on mobile */                           
            .hero { 
                height: 100vh;                          /* May cause scrolling on mobile */   
            }     
            /* SOLUTION - use min-height or newer units */  
            .hero { 
                min-height: 100vh;                      /* Better */  
                height: 100dvh;                         /* Dynamic viewport height (new) */  
                height: 100svh;                         /* Small viewport height (new) */    
                height: 100lvh;                         /* Large viewport height (new) */    
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <h3>Hands-On Exercise: Convert Desktop Layout to Mobile-First</h3>
    <b>Task:</b> Take a desktop-focused layout and rebuild it using mobile-first principles<br/><br/>
    
    <b>Given Desktop-First CSS:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* Desktop styles (default) */
            .container {
                max-width: 1200px;
                margin: 0 auto;
                display: grid;
                grid-template-columns: 250px 1fr 250px;
                gap: 2rem;
            }
            h1 {
                font-size: 3rem;
                margin-bottom: 2rem;
            }
            /* Tablet */
            @media (max-width: 1024px) {
                .container {
                    grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;
                    gap: 1.5rem;
                }
                .sidebar-right {
                    display: none;
                }
            }
            /* Mobile */
            @media (max-width: 768px) {
                .container {
                    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
                    gap: 1rem;
                    padding: 1rem;
                }
                .sidebar-left {
                    display: none;
                }
                h1 {
                    font-size: 2rem;
                    margin-bottom: 1rem;
                }
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Requirements for Mobile-First Conversion:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        1. Start with mobile styles as default<br/>
        2. Use <pre>min-width</pre> media queries<br/>
        3. Implement fluid typography<br/>
        4. Use relative units (rem, em, %) instead of px<br/>
        5. Make sidebars appear/disappear appropriately<br/>
        6. Add hamburger menu for mobile navigation<br/>
        7. Ensure touch targets are at least 44√ó44px on mobile
    </div>
    
    <b>CSS Challenge:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #fff0e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Step 1:</b> Start with mobile layout (single column)<br/>
        <b>Step 2:</b> Add hamburger menu and hide sidebars<br/>
        <b>Step 3:</b> Use appropriate mobile typography sizes<br/>
        <b>Step 4:</b> Add tablet breakpoint (768px) - show left sidebar<br/>
        <b>Step 5:</b> Add desktop breakpoint (1024px) - show both sidebars<br/>
        <b>Step 6:</b> Use fluid spacing with clamp()<br/>
        <b>Step 7:</b> Test on multiple viewport sizes
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <h3>Common Responsive Design Mistakes</h3>
    
    <b>Mistake 1: Too Many Breakpoints</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* WRONG - breakpoints for every device */  
            @media (min-width: 320px) { ... }   
            @media (min-width: 375px) { ... }   
            @media (min-width: 414px) { ... }   
            @media (min-width: 480px) { ... }   
            @media (min-width: 640px) { ... }   
            /* etc... */       
            /* RIGHT - breakpoints where layout actually changes */ 
