    <p>Today we'll learn how to create visually rich, performant designs with images and backgrounds.</p>
    
    <div class="analogy-box">
        <b>Analogy: Theater Stage Production üé≠</b><br/>
        <ul style="margin-top: 10px;">
            <li><b>Images</b> = Lead actors (front and center)</li>
            <li><b>Backgrounds</b> = Stage backdrop and scenery</li>
            <li><b>Gradients</b> = Mood lighting</li>
            <li><b>Layering</b> = Foreground, middle ground, background</li>
            <li><b>Responsive Images</b> = Actors that adapt to different theaters</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <h3>Key Topics</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Responsive Images & Performance</li>
        <li>CSS Background Properties</li>
        <li>Gradients & Multiple Backgrounds</li>
        <li>Object-fit & Object-position</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>In-Depth Explanation</h3>
    
    <b>a. Responsive Images - Performance Matters!</b><br/>
    
    <b>The Problem:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            &lt;!-- WRONG - loads huge image on mobile --&gt;
            &lt;img src="large-2000px.jpg" alt="Photo"&gt;
            <b>Issues:</b>
            1. <b>Slow loading</b> on mobile (3G/4G)
            2. <b>Wasted bandwidth</b> (mobile doesn't need 2000px)
            3. <b>Poor performance</b> affects SEO and user experience
            4. <b>Data cost</b> for users with limited plans
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Solution 1: srcset & sizes Attributes</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            &lt;img
                src="image-small.jpg"
                srcset="
                    image-small.jpg 400w,
                    image-medium.jpg 800w,
                    image-large.jpg 1200w,
                    image-xlarge.jpg 2000w
                "
                sizes="
                    (max-width: 600px) 400px,
                    (max-width: 1200px) 800px,
                    1200px
                "
                alt="Responsive image example"
            &gt;
        </pre>
        <small><b>How it works:</b> Browser chooses the best image based on screen size and pixel density</small>
    </div>
    
    <b>Solution 2: Picture Element (Art Direction)</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            &lt;picture&gt;
                &lt;!-- Mobile: square crop --&gt;
                &lt;source 
                    media="(max-width: 768px)"
                    srcset="image-square-small.jpg 1x, image-square-large.jpg 2x"
                &gt;
                &lt;!-- Desktop: wide crop --&gt;
                &lt;source 
                    media="(min-width: 769px)"
                    srcset="image-wide-small.jpg 1x, image-wide-large.jpg 2x"
                &gt;
                &lt;!-- Fallback --&gt;
                &lt;img src="image-default.jpg" alt="Art directed image"&gt;
            &lt;/picture&gt;
        </pre>
        <small><b>Use when:</b> You need different crops or compositions for different screen sizes</small>
    </div>
    
    <b>Solution 3: Modern Image Formats</b>
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>WebP:</b> 25-35% smaller than JPEG <br />
        <b>AVIF:</b> 50% smaller than JPEG (newest) <br />
        <b>Usage:</b><br/>
        <pre>
            &lt;picture&gt;<br/>
                &lt;source srcset="image.avif" type="image/avif"&gt;<br/>
                &lt;source srcset="image.webp" type="image/webp"&gt;<br/>
                &lt;img src="image.jpg" alt="Modern formats"&gt;<br/>
            &lt;/picture&gt;
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Image Optimization Checklist:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #fff0e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        ‚úÖ Use appropriate format (JPEG for photos, PNG for graphics, SVG for icons)<br/>
        ‚úÖ Compress images (tools: TinyPNG, Squoosh, ImageOptim)<br/>
        ‚úÖ Specify width and height attributes to prevent layout shifts<br/>
        ‚úÖ Use lazy loading: <pre>&lt;img loading="lazy"&gt;</pre><br/>
        ‚úÖ Consider CDN for faster delivery<br/>
        ‚úÖ Use CSS for decorative images (backgrounds)
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>b. CSS Background Properties - The "Stage Backdrop"</b><br/>
    
    <b>Background Shorthand:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* Long form */
            .element {
                background-color: #000;
                background-image: url('image.jpg');
                background-repeat: no-repeat;
                background-position: center center;
                background-size: cover;
                background-attachment: fixed;
            }
            /* Shorthand (order matters!) */
            .element {
                background: #000 url('image.jpg') no-repeat center center / cover fixed;
                /* color image repeat position / size attachment */
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Background Properties Explained:</b>
    <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 15px 0;">
        <tr style="background-color: #f0f0f0;">
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Property</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Values</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Example</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Effect</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
