    <b>c. Gradients & Multiple Backgrounds</b><br/>
    
    <b>Linear Gradients:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* Basic syntax */
            background: linear-gradient(direction, color-stop1, color-stop2, ...);
            /* Examples: */
            .gradient1 {
                background: linear-gradient(to right, red, blue);
            }
            .gradient2 {
                background: linear-gradient(45deg, red, orange, yellow, green, blue, indigo, violet);
            }
            .gradient3 {
                background: linear-gradient(to bottom right, rgba(255,0,0,0.8), rgba(0,0,255,0.8));
            }
            /* With color stops */
            .gradient4 {
                background: linear-gradient(to right, red 0%, red 50%, blue 50%, blue 100%);
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Radial Gradients:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* Basic syntax */
            background: radial-gradient(shape size at position, start-color, ..., last-color);
            /* Examples: */
            .radial1 {
                background: radial-gradient(circle, red, yellow, green);
            }
            .radial2 {
                background: radial-gradient(ellipse at center, red 0%, yellow 50%, green 100%);
            }
            .radial3 {
                background: radial-gradient(circle at top left, red, transparent 50%);
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Conic Gradients (New!):</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* Color wheel */
            .conic1 {
                background: conic-gradient(red, yellow, lime, aqua, blue, magenta, red);
