    <b>d. Object-fit & Object-position</b><br/>
    
    <b>The Problem with Images in Containers:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* WRONG - image gets distorted */
            .container {
                width: 300px;
                height: 200px;
            }
            .container img {
                width: 100%;
                height: 100%;
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Solution: object-fit (like background-size for images)</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            .container img {
                width: 100%;
                height: 100%;
                object-fit: cover;  /* Like background-size: cover */
                object-position: center;    /* Like background-position */
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Object-fit Values:</b>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 10px; margin: 15px 0;">
        <div style="text-align: center;">
            <div style="width: 120px; height: 80px; margin: 0 auto; border: 2px solid #ccc; overflow: hidden;">
                <div style="width: 100%; height: 100%; background: linear-gradient(45deg, #ff9999 25%, #99ff99 25%, #99ff99 50%, #ff9999 50%, #ff9999 75%, #99ff99 75%);"></div>
            </div>
            <small><code>object-fit: fill</code><br/>(default, stretches)</small>
        </div>
        <div style="text-align: center;">
            <div style="width: 120px; height: 80px; margin: 0 auto; border: 2px solid #ccc; overflow: hidden; position: relative;">
                <div style="width: 60px; height: 60px; background: linear-gradient(45deg, #ff9999, #99ff99); position: absolute; top: 50%; left: 50%; transform: translate(-50%, -50%);"></div>
            </div>
            <small><code>object-fit: contain</code><br/>(fits whole image)</small>
        </div>
        <div style="text-align: center;">
            <div style="width: 120px; height: 80px; margin: 0 auto; border: 2px solid #ccc; overflow: hidden;">
                <div style="width: 150px; height: 100px; background: linear-gradient(45deg, #ff9999, #99ff99); margin-left: -15px;"></div>
            </div>
            <small><code>object-fit: cover</code><br/>(fills, may crop)</small>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <b>Practical Use Cases:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        1. <b>Profile pictures:</b> <code>object-fit: cover</code> to maintain square crop<br/>
        2. <b>Product images:</b> <code>object-fit: contain</code> to show entire product<br/>
        3. <b>Hero images:</b> <code>object-fit: cover</code> with <code>object-position: top</code><br/>
        4. <b>Logo grids:</b> <code>object-fit: scale-down</code> to fit without stretching<br/>
        5. <b>Gallery thumbs:</b> <code>object-fit: cover</code> with fixed aspect ratio
    </div>
    
