    <h3>Common Visual Design Mistakes</h3>
    
    <b>Mistake 1: Poor Image Optimization</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* WRONG - loading 5MB image on mobile */
            &lt;img src="huge-uncompressed-photo.jpg"&gt;
            /* RIGHT - optimized and responsive */
            &lt;img
                src="photo-400.jpg"
                srcset="photo-400.jpg 400w, photo-800.jpg 800w, photo-1200.jpg 1200w"
                sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 50vw"
                alt="Optimized image"
                loading="lazy"
            &gt;
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Mistake 2: Distorted Images</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* WRONG - distorts images */
            .card img {
                width: 300px;
                height: 200px;
            }
            /* RIGHT - maintains aspect ratio */
            .card img {
                width: 100%;
                height: 200px;
                object-fit: cover;
                object-position: center;
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Mistake 3: Overusing Background Images</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            /* WRONG - content images as backgrounds */
            .product {
