            "4-1": {
                icon: "fa-palette",
                title: "UI/UX Principles & Visual Hierarchy",
                html: `<h1>Week 4, Day 1: UI/UX Principles & Visual Hierarchy</h1>
    <p>Today we'll learn how to make websites not just functional, but intuitive and beautiful through UI/UX design principles.</p>
    
    <div class="analogy-box">
        <b>Analogy: Designing a Restaurant Experience üçΩÔ∏è</b><br/>
        
        UI (User Interface): The menu design, table layout, decor<br/>
        UX (User Experience): How easy it is to order, wait time, service quality<br/>
        Visual Hierarchy: Putting "Chef's Special" at the top of the menu<br/>
        Proximity: Grouping appetizers together, entrees together<br/>
        Contrast: Using red for "Spicy" warnings<br/>
        White Space: Leaving space between menu sections<br/>
        Consistency: Same font and colors throughout the menu<br/>
        Affordance: Making buttons look clickable
    </div>

    <h3>Key Topics</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Difference between UI and UX</li>
        <li>7 Core UI/UX Principles</li>
        <li>Creating Visual Hierarchy</li>
        <li>Using White Space Effectively</li>
        <li>Designing for Accessibility</li>
        <li>Practical Design Exercises</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>In-Depth Explanation</h3>
    
    <b>a. UI vs UX: What's the Difference?</b>
    
    <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 15px 0;">
        <tr style="background-color: #f0f0f0;">
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Aspect</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">UI (User Interface)</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">UX (User Experience)</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Focus</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">How it looks</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">How it works/feels</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Analogies</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Car paint, interior</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Driving experience</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Elements</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Buttons, colors, typography</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">User flow, emotions, efficiency</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Tools</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Figma, Sketch, Adobe XD</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">User testing, interviews</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Goal</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Aesthetic appeal</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">User satisfaction</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    
    <b>Key Insight:</b> Good UI makes it beautiful, good UX makes it easy. Great design needs both!
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>b. 7 Core UI/UX Principles</b>
    
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>1. Visual Hierarchy</b><br/>
        <i>"What should users see first?"</i><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Size: Larger elements grab attention first<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Color: Bright colors stand out more<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Position: Top/left gets seen first (F-pattern reading)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Contrast: High contrast = more important<br/>
        
        <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 10px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
            <pre>
                /* Bad hierarchy */<br/>
                h1 { font-size: 16px; color: #666; }<br/>
                p { font-size: 24px; color: #000; }<br/>
                <br/>
                /* Good hierarchy */<br/>
                h1 { font-size: 32px; color: #000; font-weight: bold; }<br/>
                h2 { font-size: 24px; color: #333; }<br/>
                p { font-size: 16px; color: #666; }
            </pre>
        </div>
        
        <b>2. Proximity & Grouping</b><br/>
        <i>"Related things should be close together"</i><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Group related elements (forms, navigation)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Separate unrelated elements<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Use spacing to show relationships<br/>
        
        <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 10px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
            <pre>
                /* Bad proximity */<br/>
                label { margin-bottom: 30px; }<br/>
                input { margin-top: 30px; }<br/>
                <br/>
                /* Good proximity */<br/>
                .form-group {<br/>
                    margin-bottom: 20px;<br/>
                }<br/>
                label {<br/>
                    display: block;<br/>
                    margin-bottom: 5px;<br/>
                }<br/>
                input {<br/>
                    display: block;<br/>
                    width: 100%;<br/>
                }
            </pre>
        </div>
        
        <b>3. Contrast</b><br/>
        <i>"Make important elements stand out"</i><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Color contrast for readability<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Size contrast for importance<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Style contrast for differentiation<br/>
        
        <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 10px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
            <pre>
                /* Bad contrast */<br/>
                .button {<br/>
                    background: #f0f0f0;<br/>
                    color: #e0e0e0;<br/>
                }<br/>
                <br/>
                /* Good contrast */<br/>
                .primary-button {<br/>
                    background: #007bff;<br/>
                    color: white;<br/>
                    font-weight: bold;<br/>
                }<br/>
                .secondary-button {<br/>
                    background: #6c757d;<br/>
                    color: white;<br/>
                }
            </pre>
        </div>
        
        <b>4. Consistency</b><br/>
        <i>"Don't make users learn new patterns"</i><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Use same colors, fonts, buttons throughout<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Maintain consistent spacing<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Follow platform conventions<br/>
        
        <b>5. White Space (Negative Space)</b><br/>
        <i>"Give elements room to breathe"</i><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Improves readability by 20%<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Guides user's eye<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Makes content less overwhelming<br/>
        
        <b>6. Affordance</b><br/>
        <i>"Make it obvious what things do"</i><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Buttons should look clickable<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Links should look like links<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Form fields should look editable<br/>
        
        <b>7. Feedback</b><br/>
        <i>"Tell users what's happening"</i><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Loading states<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Success/error messages<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Hover effects<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Click/tap feedback
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>c. The F-Pattern & Z-Pattern Reading</b>
    
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 20px; margin: 20px 0;">
        <div style="flex: 1; background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
            <b>F-Pattern (Content-heavy)</b><br/>
            ‚Ä¢ Users scan top horizontally<br/>
            ‚Ä¢ Then down and scan middle<br/>
            ‚Ä¢ Then down and scan bottom<br/>
            ‚Ä¢ <b>Best for:</b> Blogs, articles, news<br/>
            ‚Ä¢ <b>Place:</b> Logo top-left, navigation top, key info along F-path
        </div>
        <div style="flex: 1; background-color: #fff0f0; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
            <b>Z-Pattern (Simple pages)</b><br/>
            ‚Ä¢ Users scan top left to right<br/>
            ‚Ä¢ Diagonal down to left<br/>
            ‚Ä¢ Bottom left to right<br/>
            ‚Ä¢ <b>Best for:</b> Landing pages, portfolios<br/>
            ‚Ä¢ <b>Place:</b> Logo top-left, CTA bottom-right, key points along Z-path
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Implementation Example:</b><br/>
        <pre>
            /* F-Pattern Layout */<br/>
            .content-page {<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;max-width: 800px;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;margin: 0 auto;<br/>
            }<br/>
            .main-heading {<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;margin-top: 40px;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;margin-bottom: 20px;<br/>
            }<br/>
            .subheading {<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;margin-top: 30px;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;margin-bottom: 15px;<br/>
            }<br/>
            .key-point {<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;margin-left: 20px;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;font-weight: bold;<br/>
            }<br/>
            <br/>
            /* Z-Pattern Layout */<br/>
            .landing-page {<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;text-align: center;<br/>
            }<br/>
            .hero {<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;padding: 100px 20px;<br/>
            }<br/>
            .features {<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;display: flex;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;justify-content: space-around;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;margin: 50px 0;<br/>
            }<br/>
            .cta-section {<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;padding: 80px 20px;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;background: #f8f9fa;<br/>
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>d. Accessibility in Design (WCAG Basics)</b>
    
    <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>WCAG = Web Content Accessibility Guidelines</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Makes websites usable for everyone<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Legal requirement in many countries<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Improves SEO and user experience<br/>
        
        <b>4 Key Principles (POUR):</b><br/>
        1. <b>Perceivable</b>: Can users perceive the content?<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;‚Ä¢ Alt text for images<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;‚Ä¢ Captions for videos<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;‚Ä¢ Good color contrast<br/>
        
        2. <b>Operable</b>: Can users operate the interface?<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;‚Ä¢ Keyboard navigation<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;‚Ä¢ Enough time to read<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;‚Ä¢ No flashing content<br/>
        
        3. <b>Understandable</b>: Can users understand the content?<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;‚Ä¢ Clear language<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;‚Ä¢ Consistent navigation<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;‚Ä¢ Helpful error messages<br/>
        
        4. <b>Robust</b>: Works with assistive technologies?<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;‚Ä¢ Semantic HTML<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;‚Ä¢ ARIA labels when needed<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;‚Ä¢ Valid code<br/>
    </div>
    
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Accessibility Implementation:</b><br/>
        <pre>
            /* Color Contrast */<br/>
            .good-contrast {<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;color: #000000;       /* Text color */<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;background: #ffffff;  /* Background */<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;/* Contrast ratio: 21:1 (Excellent) */<br/>
            }<br/>
            <br/>
            /* Focus States for Keyboard Users */<br/>
            button:focus,<br/>
            a:focus,<br/>
            input:focus {<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;outline: 3px solid #007bff;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;outline-offset: 2px;<br/>
            }<br/>
            <br/>
            /* Semantic HTML for Screen Readers */<br/>
            &lt;nav aria-label="Main navigation"&gt;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;ul&gt;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/"&gt;Home&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/about"&gt;About&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/ul&gt;<br/>
            &lt;/nav&gt;<br/>
            <br/>
            /* Skip to Main Content Link (Hidden until focused) */<br/>
            .skip-link {<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;position: absolute;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;top: -40px;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;left: 0;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;background: #000;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;color: white;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;padding: 8px;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;z-index: 100;<br/>
            }<br/>
            .skip-link:focus {<br/>
