            "4-3": {
                icon: "fa-image",
                title: "SVG vs Raster & Image Optimization",
                html: `<h1>Week 4, Day 3: SVG vs Raster & Image Optimization</h1>
    <p>Today we'll learn about different image formats, when to use each, and how to optimize images for web performance.</p>
    
    <div class="analogy-box">
        <b>Analogy: Digital vs Physical Art üé®</b><br/>
        
        Raster Images (PNG/JPG): Like photographs or paintings<br/>
        SVG (Scalable Vector Graphics): Like math-based drawings<br/>
        Pixels: Tiny colored squares (like mosaic tiles)<br/>
        Vectors: Mathematical equations (like connect-the-dots)<br/>
        Compression: Making files smaller (like vacuum packing)<br/>
        Lossy vs Lossless: Throwing away details vs keeping everything<br/>
        Responsive Images: Right size for each device (like different clothing sizes)
    </div>

    <h3>Key Topics</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Raster vs Vector Graphics</li>
        <li>Image Formats: JPG, PNG, GIF, WebP, SVG</li>
        <li>Image Optimization Techniques</li>
        <li>Responsive Images Implementation</li>
        <li>Image Compression Tools</li>
        <li>Accessible Images & Alt Text</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>In-Depth Explanation</h3>
    
    <b>a. Raster Images: The Pixel-Based Format</b>
    
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>What are Raster Images?</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Made of a grid of pixels (picture elements)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Each pixel has a color value<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Resolution-dependent (fixed dimensions)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Best for: Photos, complex images<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Common formats: JPG, PNG, GIF, WebP<br/><br/>
        
        <b>How They Work:</b><br/>
        <div style="text-align: center; margin: 10px 0;">
            <div style="display: inline-block; background: #f0f0f0; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px;">
                <div style="font-size: 12px; font-family: monospace;">
                    200px √ó 200px Image = 40,000 pixels<br/>
                    Each pixel = 3-4 bytes (RGB/RGBA)<br/>
                    File size = 40,000 √ó 3 = 120,000 bytes<br/>
                    ‚âà 117 KB (uncompressed)
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 15px 0;">
        <tr style="background-color: #f0f0f0;">
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Format</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Best For</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Compression</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Transparency</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Animation</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Example Use</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>JPG/JPEG</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Photographs</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Lossy (adjustable)</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">‚ùå No</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">‚ùå No</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Product photos</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>PNG</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Logos, graphics</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Lossless</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">‚úÖ Yes (PNG-24)</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">‚ùå No</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Logos with transparency</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>GIF</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Simple animations</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Lossless</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">‚úÖ Yes (1-bit)</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">‚úÖ Yes</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Simple animations, memes</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>WebP</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Modern alternative</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Both</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">‚úÖ Yes</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">‚úÖ Yes</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Everything (if supported)</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Code Examples:</b><br/>
        <pre>
            &lt;!-- JPG for photographs --&gt;
            &lt;img src="photo.jpg" alt="Beautiful landscape" width="800" height="600"&gt;
            
            &lt;!-- PNG for logos with transparency --&gt;
            &lt;img src="logo.png" alt="Company logo" width="200" height="100"&gt;
            
            &lt;!-- GIF for simple animations --&gt;
            &lt;img src="loading.gif" alt="Loading animation" width="50" height="50"&gt;
            
            &lt;!-- WebP with fallback --&gt;
            &lt;picture&gt;
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;source srcset="image.webp" type="image/webp"&gt;
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;img src="image.jpg" alt="Description"&gt;
            &lt;/picture&gt;
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>b. SVG: Scalable Vector Graphics</b>
    
    <div style="background-color: #fff0f0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>What are SVG Files?</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ XML-based vector image format<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Defined by mathematical equations<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Resolution-independent (infinitely scalable)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Best for: Icons, logos, simple graphics<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ File extension: .svg<br/><br/>
        
        <b>Key Advantages:</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>Scalable</b> to any size without quality loss<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>Small file size</b> for simple graphics<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>Editable with code</b> (CSS/JavaScript)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>Accessible</b> (screen reader friendly)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>Animatable</b> with CSS/JavaScript<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>Search engine friendly</b> (text in SVG is readable)
    </div>
    
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Basic SVG Structure:</b><br/>
        <pre>
            &lt;!-- Simple SVG --&gt;
            &lt;svg width="100" height="100" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;
                &lt;circle cx="50" cy="50" r="40" stroke="black" stroke-width="3" fill="red" /&gt;
            &lt;/svg&gt;
            
            &lt;!-- More complex SVG --&gt;
            &lt;svg width="200" height="200" viewBox="0 0 200 200"&gt;
                &lt;rect x="10" y="10" width="180" height="180" fill="blue" /&gt;
                &lt;path d="M20,20 L180,20 L100,180 Z" fill="yellow" /&gt;
                &lt;text x="100" y="100" text-anchor="middle" fill="white"&gt;SVG&lt;/text&gt;
            &lt;/svg&gt;
            
            &lt;!-- SVG as image --&gt;
            &lt;img src="logo.svg" alt="Logo" width="200" height="100"&gt;
            
            &lt;!-- Inline SVG --&gt;
            &lt;button&gt;
                &lt;svg width="20" height="20"&gt;
                    &lt;path d="M10 0 L20 10 L10 20 L0 10 Z" fill="currentColor" /&gt;
                &lt;/svg&gt;
                Settings
            &lt;/button&gt;
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin: 20px 0;">
        <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
            <b>When to Use SVG:</b><br/>
            ‚úì Logos and icons<br/>
            ‚úì Simple illustrations<br/>
            ‚úì Data visualizations (charts)<br/>
            ‚úì UI elements (buttons, badges)<br/>
            ‚úì Animations and interactions<br/>
            ‚úì When you need to change colors with CSS<br/>
            ‚úì When you need responsive scaling
        </div>
        
        <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
            <b>When NOT to Use SVG:</b><br/>
            ‚úó Photographs<br/>
            ‚úó Complex images with many colors<br/>
            ‚úó Images with fine details<br/>
            ‚úó When file size would be larger than raster<br/>
            ‚úó When browser support is critical (very rare now)<br/>
            ‚úó When you can't edit the SVG code
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>c. Image Optimization Techniques</b>
    
    <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Why Optimize Images?</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>Faster page loads</b> (users leave if pages are slow)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>Better SEO</b> (Google ranks faster sites higher)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>Reduced bandwidth costs</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>Better user experience</b> (especially on mobile)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>Environmental impact</b> (less energy consumption)<br/><br/>
        
        <b>Goal: Smallest file size + Acceptable quality</b>
    </div>
    
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Optimization Checklist:</b><br/>
        <pre>
            1. <b>Right Format:</b> JPG for photos, PNG for graphics, SVG for vectors<br/>
            2. <b>Right Dimensions:</b> Serve images at display size<br/>
            3. <b>Compression:</b> Use tools to reduce file size<br/>
            4. <b>Lazy Loading:</b> Load images as needed<br/>
            5. <b>Responsive Images:</b> Serve different sizes for different devices<br/>
            6. <b>CDN:</b> Use Content Delivery Networks<br/>
            7. <b>Caching:</b> Set proper cache headers<br/>
            8. <b>Modern Formats:</b> Use WebP when possible
        </pre>
    </div>
    
