    <b>d. Responsive Images Implementation</b>
    
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>The Problem:</b> Serving a 2000px wide image to a 320px wide phone wastes bandwidth!<br/><br/>
        
        <b>Solution 1: CSS Responsive Images</b><br/>
        <pre>
            img {
                max-width: 100%;
                height: auto; /* Maintain aspect ratio */
            }
            
            /* For background images */
            .hero {
                background-image: url('image.jpg');
                background-size: cover;
                background-position: center;
            }
        </pre>
        
        <b>Solution 2: HTML srcset Attribute</b>
        <pre>
            &lt;img src="image-400.jpg"
                &nbsp;srcset="image-400.jpg 400w,
                            &nbsp;image-800.jpg 800w,
                            &nbsp;image-1200.jpg 1200w"
                &nbsp;sizes="(max-width: 600px) 400px,
                            &nbsp;800px"
                &nbsp;alt="Responsive image"&gt;
        </pre>
        
        <b>Solution 3: Picture Element (Art Direction)</b>
        <pre>
            &lt;picture&gt;
                &lt;!-- Mobile crop (square) --&gt;
                &lt;source media="(max-width: 768px)"
                    srcset="image-square-400.jpg 1x,
                            image-square-800.jpg 2x"&gt;
                &lt;!-- Desktop (landscape) --&gt;
                &lt;source media="(min-width: 769px)"
                    srcset="image-landscape-800.jpg 1x,
                            image-landscape-1600.jpg 2x"&gt;
                &lt;!-- Fallback --&gt;
                &lt;img src="image.jpg" alt="Art directed image"&gt;
            &lt;/picture&gt;
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Modern Image Formats (WebP/AVIF):</b>
        <pre>
            &lt;picture&gt;
                &lt;!-- AVIF (best compression) --&gt;
                &lt;source type="image/avif" srcset="image.avif"&gt;
                &lt;!-- WebP (good compression, better support) --&gt;
                &lt;source type="image/webp" srcset="image.webp"&gt;
                &lt;!-- Fallback to JPEG --&gt;
                &lt;img src="image.jpg" alt="Modern image format example"&gt;
            &lt;/picture&gt;
            
            /* Browser Support Check */
            const supportsWebP = () => {
                const canvas = document.createElement('canvas');
                if (canvas.getContext && canvas.getContext('2d')) {
                    return canvas.toDataURL('image/webp').indexOf('data:image/webp') == 0;
                }
                return false;
            };
        </pre>
    </div>
    
