        <b>Color Properties:</b><br/>
        1. <b>Hue:</b> The color itself (red, blue, green)<br/>
        2. <b>Saturation:</b> Intensity/purity of the color<br/>
        3. <b>Brightness/Lightness:</b> How light or dark the color is<br/>
        4. <b>Value:</b> Relative lightness or darkness<br/>
    </div>


    
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin: 20px 0;">
        <div style="background-color: #fff0f0; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
            <b>Color Models:</b><br/>
            <b>RGB (Red, Green, Blue):</b><br/>
            ‚Ä¢ Additive color (light)<br/>
            ‚Ä¢ Used for screens<br/>
            ‚Ä¢ 0-255 each channel<br/>
            <code>rgb(255, 0, 0) = Red</code><br/><br/>
            
            <b>HEX:</b><br/>
            ‚Ä¢ Shorthand for RGB<br/>
            ‚Ä¢ #RRGGBB format<br/>
            ‚Ä¢ 00-FF each channel<br/>
            <code>#FF0000 = Red</code>
        </div>
        
        <div style="background-color: #f0fff0; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
            <b>HSL (Hue, Saturation, Lightness):</b><br/>
            ‚Ä¢ More intuitive for design<br/>
            ‚Ä¢ Easier to create variations<br/>
            ‚Ä¢ Hue: 0-360¬∞ (color wheel)<br/>
            ‚Ä¢ Saturation: 0-100% (intensity)<br/>
            ‚Ä¢ Lightness: 0-100% (brightness)<br/>
            <code>hsl(0, 100%, 50%) = Red</code><br/><br/>
            
            <b>HSLA:</b><br/>
            ‚Ä¢ HSL with transparency<br/>
            <code>hsla(0, 100%, 50%, 0.5) = Semi-transparent red</code>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 15px 0;">
