    <hr/>
    
    <b>b. Creating Effective Color Palettes</b>
    
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>The 60-30-10 Rule for Web Design:</b><br/>
        <pre>
            ‚Ä¢ <b>60%</b> Dominant Color: Background, large areas
            ‚Ä¢ <b>30%</b> Secondary Color: Sidebars, secondary elements
            ‚Ä¢ <b>10%</b> Accent Color: Buttons, links, CTAs
            <br/>
            Example for a website:<br/>
            ‚Ä¢ 60%: White or light gray background
            ‚Ä¢ 30%: Dark gray for text and headers
            ‚Ä¢ 10%: Brand color for buttons and links
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <div style="background-color: #f5f0ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Building a Color Palette:</b><br/>
        
        <b>Step 1: Choose a Base Color</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Start with your brand color or primary color<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Use color psychology to guide choice<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Example: Blue for trust, Green for growth<br/><br/>
        
        <b>Step 2: Create Variations</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Lighten (tints) for backgrounds<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Darken (shades) for text<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Adjust saturation for accents<br/><br/>
        
        <b>Step 3: Add Complementary Colors</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Choose harmony scheme<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Add 2-3 additional colors<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Ensure good contrast<br/><br/>
        
        <b>Step 4: Add Neutrals</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Black, white, grays<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ For text, borders, backgrounds<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Ensure accessibility
    </div>
    
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>CSS Color System Example:</b><br/>
        <pre>
            :root {
                /* Primary Colors */
                --color-primary: #007bff;
                --color-primary-light: #3395ff;
