        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>c. WCAG Accessibility Guidelines</b>
    
    <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>WCAG = Web Content Accessibility Guidelines</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ International standard for web accessibility<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Created by W3C (World Wide Web Consortium)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Legal requirement in many countries<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Benefits everyone, not just people with disabilities<br/><br/>
        
        <b>WCAG Principles (POUR):</b><br/>
        1. <b>Perceivable</b> - Can users perceive the content?<br/>
        2. <b>Operable</b> - Can users operate the interface?<br/>
        3. <b>Understandable</b> - Can users understand the content?<br/>
        4. <b>Robust</b> - Can various technologies access the content?<br/><br/>
        
        <b>WCAG Levels:</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>A</b> - Basic accessibility (must satisfy)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>AA</b> - Good accessibility (should satisfy)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>AAA</b> - Excellent accessibility (may satisfy)
    </div>
    
    <div style="background-color: #fff0f0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>WCAG Color & Contrast Requirements (AA Level):</b><br/>
        
        <b>1. Color Contrast:</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>Normal text:</b> 4.5:1 contrast ratio<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>Large text (18pt+ or 14pt+bold):</b> 3:1 contrast ratio<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>UI components:</b> 3:1 contrast ratio<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>Graphics/charts:</b> 3:1 contrast ratio<br/><br/>
        
        <b>2. Color Independence:</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Color cannot be the only means of conveying information<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Example: Required fields marked only in red = ‚ùå<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Solution: Add an asterisk or "required" text<br/><br/>
        
        <b>3. Color Blindness:</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Ensure information works in grayscale<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Test with color blindness simulators<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Use patterns/textures in addition to colors
    </div>
    
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Calculating Contrast Ratio:</b><br/>
        <pre>
            Contrast Ratio = (L1 + 0.05) / (L2 + 0.05)
            Where:
            ‚Ä¢ L1 = Relative luminance of lighter color
            ‚Ä¢ L2 = Relative luminance of darker color
            ‚Ä¢ Values range from 1:1 (no contrast) to 21:1 (maximum)
            
            Example: Black text on white background
            ‚Ä¢ Black: L = 0.0
            ‚Ä¢ White: L = 1.0
            ‚Ä¢ Ratio = (1.0 + 0.05) / (0.0 + 0.05) = 21:1 ‚úì
            
            /* CSS function for checking contrast */
            @media (prefers-contrast: high) {
                body {
                    --text-color: #000000;
                    --background-color: #ffffff;
                }
            }
            
            /* JavaScript calculation */
            function getContrastRatio(color1, color2) {
                const l1 = getRelativeLuminance(color1);
                const l2 = getRelativeLuminance(color2);
                return (Math.max(l1, l2) + 0.05) / (Math.min(l1, l2) + 0.05);
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>d. Designing for Color Blindness</b>
    
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Types of Color Vision Deficiency (Color Blindness):</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>8% of men</b> and <b>0.5% of women</b> have some form<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>Protanopia:</b> Red-green (cannot see red well)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>Deuteranopia:</b> Red-green (most common)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>Tritanopia:</b> Blue-yellow (rare)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>Achromatopsia:</b> Complete color blindness (very rare)<br/><br/>
        
        <b>Problem Colors:</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Red & Green (look similar)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Blue & Purple (look similar)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Pink & Gray (look similar)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Light Green & Yellow (look similar)
    </div>
    
    <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 15px 0;">
        <tr style="background-color: #f0f0f0;">
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Problem</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Bad Example</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Good Solution</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Implementation</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Traffic Lights</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Red/Yellow/Green only</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Add position + symbols</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Top=Stop, Middle=Caution, Bottom=Go</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Form Errors</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Red text only</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Icon + text + color</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">‚ö†Ô∏è Error: Field is required</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Charts/Graphs</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Different colors only</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Patterns + labels</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Stripes, dots, numbers on bars</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Links in Text</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Blue color only</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Underline + color</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Blue text with underline</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Required Fields</b></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Red asterisk only</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Text label + asterisk</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">(required) or asterisk with title</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Testing for Color Blindness:</b><br/>
        <pre>
            /* CSS filter to simulate color blindness */
            .protanopia-simulation {
                filter: url('#protanopia');
            }
            
            /* In SVG filter definition */
            &lt;svg style="display: none;"&gt;
                &lt;filter id="protanopia"&gt;
                    &lt;feColorMatrix type="matrix"
                    values="0.567, 0.433, 0,     0, 0
                                0.558, 0.442, 0,     0, 0
                                0,     0.242, 0.758, 0, 0
                                0,     0,     0,     1, 0"/&gt;
                &lt;/filter&gt;
            &lt;/svg&gt;
            
            /* JavaScript color blindness check */
            function checkColorBlindSafe(colors) {
                // Convert to grayscale and check contrast
                const grayscaleColors = colors.map(color =>
                    0.299 * color.r + 0.587 * color.g + 0.114 * color.b
                );
                // Ensure sufficient difference in grayscale
                return Math.max(...grayscaleColors) - Math.min(...grayscaleColors) > 0.3;
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
