            "8-1": {
                icon: "fa-mouse-pointer",
                title: "DOM Selection & Element Manipulation",
                html: `<h1>Week 8, Day 1: DOM Selection & Element Manipulation</h1>
    <p>Today we'll learn how to select and manipulate HTML elements using JavaScript - the foundation of interactive web pages.</p>
    
    <div class="analogy-box">
        <b>Analogy: Construction Site Supervisor üèóÔ∏è</b><br/>
        
        <pre>DOM (Document Object Model)</pre>: Blueprint of the building<br/>
        <pre>Elements</pre>: Individual parts (doors, windows, walls)<br/>
        <pre>querySelector</pre>: Finding specific item by description<br/>
        <pre>querySelectorAll</pre>: Finding all items matching description<br/>
        <pre>Element Properties</pre>: Characteristics of each part (color, size)<br/>
        <pre>Element Methods</pre>: Actions you can perform (open, close, paint)<br/>
        <pre>DOM Traversal</pre>: Moving between related parts (room to room)
    </div>

    <h3>Key Topics</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Understanding the DOM Tree</li>
        <li>Selecting Elements: querySelector, getElementById, etc.</li>
        <li>Working with NodeLists and HTMLCollections</li>
        <li>Element Properties: innerHTML, textContent, className</li>
        <li>Element Attributes: getAttribute, setAttribute</li>
        <li>Creating & Removing Elements</li>
        <li>DOM Traversal: parent, children, siblings</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>In-Depth Explanation</h3>
    
    <b>a. Understanding the DOM</b>
    
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>What is the DOM?</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Document Object Model<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Tree-like representation of HTML document<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ JavaScript can read and modify the DOM<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Browser creates DOM from HTML<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Dynamic changes update the page instantly<br/><br/>
        
        <b>DOM Tree Structure:</b><br/>
        <pre>
            document (root)<br/>
            ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ html<br/>
            ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ head<br/>
            ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ title<br/>
            ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ meta<br/>
            ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ body<br/>
            ‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ header<br/>
            ‚îÇ       ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ h1<br/>
            ‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ main<br/>
            ‚îÇ       ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ section<br/>
            ‚îÇ       ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ div<br/>
            ‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ footer<br/>
            ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ...<br/>
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>HTML to DOM Example:</b><br/>
        <pre>
            &lt;!-- HTML --&gt;<br/>
            &lt;div id="container" class="main"&gt;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;h1 class="title"&gt;Hello World&lt;/h1&gt;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph&lt;/p&gt;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;button class="btn"&gt;Click me&lt;/button&gt;<br/>
            &lt;/div&gt;<br/>
            <br/>
            /* DOM Representation */<br/>
            {<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;tagName: 'DIV',<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;id: 'container',<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;className: 'main',<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;children: [<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;{<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;tagName: 'H1',<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;className: 'title',<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;textContent: 'Hello World'<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;},<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;{<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;tagName: 'P',<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;textContent: 'This is a paragraph'<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;},<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;{<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;tagName: 'BUTTON',<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;className: 'btn',<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;textContent: 'Click me'<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;]<br/>
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>b. Selecting DOM Elements</b>
    
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Modern Selection Methods:</b><br/>
        <pre>
            // 1. querySelector - returns FIRST matching element<br/>
            const element = document.querySelector('.className');<br/>
            const element = document.querySelector('#idName');<br/>
            const element = document.querySelector('div');<br/>
            const element = document.querySelector('div.className');<br/>
            const element = document.querySelector('#parent .child');<br/>
            <br/>
            // 2. querySelectorAll - returns ALL matching elements (NodeList)<br/>
            const elements = document.querySelectorAll('.className');<br/>
            const elements = document.querySelectorAll('div');<br/>
            const elements = document.querySelectorAll('ul li');<br/>
            <br/>
            // 3. getElementById - fastest for ID selection<br/>
            const element = document.getElementById('myId');<br/>
            <br/>
            // 4. getElementsByClassName - returns HTMLCollection<br/>
            const elements = document.getElementsByClassName('myClass');<br/>
            <br/>
            // 5. getElementsByTagName - returns HTMLCollection<br/>
            const elements = document.getElementsByTagName('div');<br/>
            <br/>
            // 6. getElementsByName - for form elements<br/>
            const elements = document.getElementsByName('username');<br/>
            <br/>
            // Complex selectors<br/>
            const element = document.querySelector('form input[type="email"]');<br/>
            const element = document.querySelector('li:first-child');<br/>
            const element = document.querySelector('p:hover'); // Doesn't work!<br/>
            const element = document.querySelector('input:checked');
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 15px 0;">
        <tr style="background-color: #f0f0f0;">
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Method</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Returns</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Live?</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Use Case</th>
            <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Performance</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">querySelector()</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Element or null</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">No</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Single element, complex selectors</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Good</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">querySelectorAll()</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">NodeList</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">No</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Multiple elements, complex selectors</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Good</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">getElementById()</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Element or null</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">N/A</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Fast ID selection</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Best</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">getElementsByClassName()</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">HTMLCollection</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Yes</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">All elements with class</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Good</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">getElementsByTagName()</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">HTMLCollection</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Yes</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">All elements by tag name</td>
            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Good</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>NodeList vs HTMLCollection:</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>NodeList:</b> Returned by querySelectorAll()<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;‚úì Has forEach method<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;‚úì Not live (static snapshot)<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;‚úì Can contain any node type<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ <b>HTMLCollection:</b> Returned by getElementsByClassName/TagName<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;‚úó No forEach (need to convert to array)<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;‚úì Live (updates as DOM changes)<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;‚úì Only contains elements<br/><br/>
        
        <b>Converting to Array:</b><br/>
        <pre>
            // NodeList to Array<br/>
            const nodeList = document.querySelectorAll('.items');<br/>
            const array1 = Array.from(nodeList);<br/>
            const array2 = [...nodeList]; // Spread operator<br/>
            <br/>
            // HTMLCollection to Array<br/>
            const htmlCollection = document.getElementsByClassName('items');<br/>
            const array3 = Array.from(htmlCollection);<br/>
            const array4 = [...htmlCollection];
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>c. Element Properties & Content</b>
    
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Content Properties:</b><br/>
        <pre>
            const element = document.querySelector('#myElement');<br/>
            <br/>
            // 1. textContent - plain text only<br/>
            element.textContent = 'New text content';<br/>
            const text = element.textContent;<br/>
            <br/>
            // 2. innerHTML - includes HTML tags<br/>
            element.innerHTML = '&lt;strong&gt;Bold text&lt;/strong&gt;';<br/>
            const html = element.innerHTML;<br/>
            <br/>
            // 3. innerText - visible text (respects CSS)<br/>
            element.innerText = 'Visible text';<br/>
            const visibleText = element.innerText;<br/>
            <br/>
            // 4. outerHTML - includes the element itself<br/>
            element.outerHTML = '&lt;div&gt;Replaces entire element&lt;/div&gt;';<br/>
            const outer = element.outerHTML;<br/>
            <br/>
            <b>Security Warning:</b><br/>
