        <h3>üéØ Day 2 Key Takeaways:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><b>addEventListener</b> is preferred over onclick for flexibility</li>
            <li>Understand <b>event propagation</b> (bubbling and capturing)</li>
            <li>Use <b>event delegation</b> for dynamic content and performance</li>
            <li>The <b>event object</b> contains valuable information about the event</li>
            <li><b>Custom events</b> enable clean communication between components</li>
            <li>Always consider <b>performance</b> (passive listeners, debouncing)</li>
            <li>Remove event listeners to prevent <b>memory leaks</b></li>
        </ul>
        
        <p><b>Event Best Practices:</b><br/>
        1. Use <b>event delegation</b> for lists and dynamic content<br/>
        2. <b>Debounce</b> or <b>throttle</b> frequent events (scroll, resize)<br/>
        3. Use <b>passive: true</b> for scroll/touch events when not calling preventDefault()<br/>
        4. Clean up event listeners when elements are removed<br/>
        5. Use <b>CustomEvent</b> for application-specific communication<br/>
        6. Consider <b>accessibility</b> (keyboard navigation, screen readers)</p>
        
        <p><b>Tomorrow:</b> We'll explore dynamic styling - adding, removing, and toggling CSS classes with JavaScript!</p>
        
