    <p>Welcome to Week 10! We're transitioning from frontend to backend development. Today we'll learn about what happens behind the scenes of web applications.</p>
    
    <div class="analogy-box">
        <b>Analogy: Restaurant Front-of-House vs Kitchen üçΩÔ∏è</b><br/>
        
        Frontend (Client-side): Dining area, menu, waiter (what users see/interact with)<br/>
        Backend (Server-side): Kitchen, chef, inventory (where the work happens)<br/>
        HTTP: The waiter carrying orders and food between kitchen and table<br/>
        Node.js: A chef who specializes in JavaScript cuisine<br/>
