    <h3>In-Depth Explanation</h3>
    
    <b>a. Frontend vs Backend: What's the Difference?</b><br/>
    
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Frontend (Client-side)</b>:
        <ul>
            <li>Runs in the user's browser</li>
            <li>Built with HTML, CSS, JavaScript</li>
            <li>Handles user interface and interactions</li>
            <li>Sends requests to backend</li>
            <li>Examples: React, Angular, Vue.js</li>
        </ul>
        
        <b>Backend (Server-side)</b>:
        <ul>
            <li>Runs on a server (not user's device)</li>
            <li>Built with Node.js, Python, Ruby, Java, PHP, etc.</li>
            <li>Handles business logic, data processing, authentication</li>
            <li>Communicates with databases</li>
            <li>Sends responses to frontend</li>
            <li>Examples: Express.js, Django, Rails, Spring</li>
        </ul>
        
        <b>Full-Stack Development</b>: Working with both frontend and backend
    </div>
    
    <b>Client-Server Architecture:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            // How it works:
            1. User visits website (frontend loads)
            2. Frontend sends HTTP request to backend
            3. Backend processes request (validates, queries database, etc.)
            4. Backend sends HTTP response with data
            5. Frontend updates UI with received data
            
            // Example: Loading user profile
            Frontend ‚Üí GET /api/users/123 ‚Üí Backend
