        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>b. Introduction to Node.js</b><br/>
    
    <b>What is Node.js?</b>
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Node.js</b>: A JavaScript runtime built on Chrome's V8 JavaScript engine<br/>
        <b>Key Features</b>:
        <ul>
            <li>Allows JavaScript to run outside the browser (on servers)</li>
            <li>Event-driven, non-blocking I/O model (highly efficient)</li>
            <li>Single-threaded with event looping</li>
            <li>Perfect for I/O-intensive applications</li>
            <li>Huge ecosystem of packages (npm)</li>
        </ul>
        
        <b>Why Node.js?</b>:
        <ul>
            <li>Use same language (JavaScript) for both frontend and backend</li>
            <li>Fast execution with V8 engine</li>
            <li>Great for real-time applications (chat, gaming)</li>
            <li>Large community and packages</li>
            <li>Excellent for APIs and microservices</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <b>Installing Node.js and npm:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            // Check if Node.js is installed
