            "10-2": {
                icon: "fa-database",
                title: "Databases & MongoDB",
                html: `<h1>Week 10, Day 2: Databases & MongoDB</h1>
    <p>Today we'll learn about databases - how to store, retrieve, and manage data for your applications.</p>
    
    <div class="analogy-box">
        <b>Analogy: Filing System vs Digital Database üìÅ</b><br/>
        
        SQL Databases: Like a filing cabinet with labeled folders (structured)<br/>
        NoSQL Databases: Like a room where you can throw documents anywhere (flexible)<br/>
        MongoDB: A digital warehouse with labeled boxes (documents)<br/>
        Database: The entire storage facility<br/>
        Collection: A shelf with similar items<br/>
        Document: A single item in a box<br/>
        Query: Asking the warehouse manager to find specific items<br/>
        Index: A catalog that helps find items faster
    </div>

    <h3>Key Topics</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>SQL vs NoSQL: Understanding the differences</li>
        <li>Introduction to MongoDB and document databases</li>
        <li>Setting up MongoDB locally and with MongoDB Atlas</li>
        <li>CRUD operations with MongoDB</li>
        <li>Data modeling for document databases</li>
        <li>Connecting Node.js to MongoDB with Mongoose</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>In-Depth Explanation</h3>
    
    <b>a. SQL vs NoSQL Databases</b><br/>
    
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse;">
            <tr style="background-color: #4a86e8; color: white;">
                <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Aspect</th>
                <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">SQL (Relational)</th>
                <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">NoSQL (Non-Relational)</th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Data Structure</b></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Tables with rows and columns<br/>Fixed schema</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Documents, key-value, graphs, wide-column<br/>Flexible schema</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Query Language</b></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">SQL (Structured Query Language)</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Varies by database (MongoDB uses JavaScript-like queries)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Scalability</b></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Vertical scaling (bigger servers)</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Horizontal scaling (more servers)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Transactions</b></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">ACID compliant (strong consistency)</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">BASE model (eventual consistency)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Best For</b></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Complex queries, financial data, reporting</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Large-scale applications, real-time data, flexible schemas</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Examples</b></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">MySQL, PostgreSQL, SQL Server, Oracle</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">MongoDB, Redis, Cassandra, CouchDB</td>
            </tr>
        </table>
        
        <b>When to Use NoSQL/MongoDB:</b>
        <ul>
            <li>Rapidly evolving data requirements</li>
            <li>Large amounts of unstructured or semi-structured data</li>
            <li>Need for horizontal scaling</li>
            <li>Real-time applications (analytics, IoT)</li>
            <li>Working with JSON-like data structures</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>b. Introduction to MongoDB</b><br/>
    
    <b>What is MongoDB?</b>
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>MongoDB</b>: A document-oriented NoSQL database<br/>
        <b>Key Features</b>:
        <ul>
            <li><b>Document Database</b>: Stores data in BSON (Binary JSON) documents</li>
            <li><b>Flexible Schema</b>: Documents in same collection can have different structures</li>
            <li><b>Scalable</b>: Horizontal scaling through sharding</li>
            <li><b>Rich Query Language</b>: Supports complex queries, aggregations, and indexing</li>
            <li><b>High Performance</b>: In-memory computing for frequently accessed data</li>
            <li><b>Geospatial Support</b>: Built-in support for location-based queries</li>
        </ul>
        
        <b>MongoDB Terminology vs SQL:</b>
        <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 10px;">
            <tr style="background-color: #4a86e8; color: white;">
                <th style="padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">SQL</th>
                <th style="padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">MongoDB</th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Database</td>
                <td style="padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Database</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Table</td>
                <td style="padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Collection</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Row</td>
                <td style="padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Document</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Column</td>
                <td style="padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Field</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Primary Key</td>
                <td style="padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">_id (ObjectId)</td>
            </tr>
        </table>
    </div>
    
    <b>Setting Up MongoDB:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            // Option 1: MongoDB Atlas (Cloud - Recommended for learning)
            // 1. Go to https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas
            // 2. Create free account (512MB storage)
            // 3. Create a cluster
            // 4. Create database user
            // 5. Get connection string
            
            // Option 2: Local Installation
            // 1. Download from https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community
            // 2. Install MongoDB Community Edition
            // 3. Start MongoDB service
            
            // Check if MongoDB is running
            mongod --version  // Check MongoDB version
            mongo --version   // Check MongoDB shell version
            
            // Start MongoDB locally (macOS/Linux)
            sudo systemctl start mongod  // or: sudo service mongod start
            
            // Start MongoDB locally (Windows)
            net start MongoDB
            
            // Connect to MongoDB shell
            mongosh  // New MongoDB shell (mongosh)
            // or
            mongo    // Legacy shell
            
            // Basic shell commands
            show dbs           // Show all databases
            use mydatabase     // Switch to/create database
            show collections   // Show collections in current database
            db.help()          // Show database commands
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Basic MongoDB Operations (Shell):</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            // Connect to MongoDB shell
            mongosh
            
            // Create/switch to database
            use bookstore
            
            // Create collection and insert documents
            db.books.insertOne({
                title: "The Great Gatsby",
                author: "F. Scott Fitzgerald",
                genre: "Fiction",
                price: 10.99,
                stock: 15,
                publishedYear: 1925,
                tags: ["classic", "american"],
                ratings: [
                    { user: "Alice", score: 5 },
                    { user: "Bob", score: 4 }
                ]
            })
            
            // Insert multiple documents
            db.books.insertMany([
                {
                    title: "To Kill a Mockingbird",
                    author: "Harper Lee",
                    genre: "Fiction",
                    price: 12.99,
                    stock: 8,
                    publishedYear: 1960
                },
                {
                    title: "1984",
                    author: "George Orwell",
                    genre: "Dystopian",
                    price: 9.99,
                    stock: 20,
                    publishedYear: 1949
                }
            ])
            
            // Find documents
            db.books.find()                      // Find all documents
            db.books.find().pretty()             // Pretty print results
            db.books.findOne()                   // Find one document
            
            // Find with conditions
            db.books.find({ genre: "Fiction" })                // Equality
            db.books.find({ price: { $lt: 12 } })              // Less than
            db.books.find({ publishedYear: { $gte: 1950 } })   // Greater than or equal
            db.books.find({ genre: { $in: ["Fiction", "Dystopian"] } }) // In array
            db.books.find({ title: /great/i })                 // Case-insensitive regex
            
            // Projection (select fields)
            db.books.find({}, { title: 1, author: 1, _id: 0 }) // Include only title and author
            
            // Update documents
            db.books.updateOne(
                { title: "The Great Gatsby" },
                { $set: { price: 11.99, stock: 10 } }
            )
            
            db.books.updateMany(
                { genre: "Fiction" },
                { $set: { discount: 0.1 } }
            )
            
            // Increment field
            db.books.updateOne(
                { title: "The Great Gatsby" },
                { $inc: { stock: 5 } }  // Increase stock by 5
            )
            
            // Add to array
            db.books.updateOne(
                { title: "The Great Gatsby" },
                { $push: { tags: "novel" } }
            )
            
            // Delete documents
            db.books.deleteOne({ title: "1984" })
            db.books.deleteMany({ stock: 0 })
            
            // Aggregation (grouping)
            db.books.aggregate([
                { $group: { 
                    _id: "$genre", 
                    count: { $sum: 1 },
                    averagePrice: { $avg: "$price" },
                    totalStock: { $sum: "$stock" }
                }}
            ])
            
            // Create index
            db.books.createIndex({ title: 1 })          // Single field index
            db.books.createIndex({ author: 1, genre: -1 }) // Compound index
            
            // Text search index
            db.books.createIndex({ title: "text", author: "text" })
            db.books.find({ $text: { $search: "great gatsby" } })
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>c. Connecting Node.js to MongoDB</b><br/>
    
    <b>Using the MongoDB Native Driver:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            // 1. Install MongoDB driver
            npm install mongodb
            
            // 2. Connect to MongoDB
            // db.js
            const { MongoClient } = require('mongodb');
            
            // Connection URI (from MongoDB Atlas)
            const uri = process.env.MONGODB_URI || 'mongodb://localhost:27017';
            
            // Database name
            const dbName = 'bookstore';
            
            let client;
            let db;
            
            async function connectToDatabase() {
                try {
                    // Create a new MongoClient
                    client = new MongoClient(uri, {
                        useNewUrlParser: true,
                        useUnifiedTopology: true
                    });
                    
                    // Connect to the MongoDB cluster
                    await client.connect();
                    console.log('Connected to MongoDB');
                    
                    // Connect to specific database
                    db = client.db(dbName);
                    
                    return db;
                } catch (error) {
                    console.error('Failed to connect to MongoDB:', error);
                    process.exit(1);
                }
            }
            
            function getDatabase() {
                if (!db) {
                    throw new Error('Database not connected. Call connectToDatabase first.');
                }
                return db;
            }
            
            async function closeConnection() {
                if (client) {
                    await client.close();
                    console.log('MongoDB connection closed');
                }
            }
            
            module.exports = {
                connectToDatabase,
                getDatabase,
                closeConnection
            };
            
            // 3. Use in your application
            // app.js
            const express = require('express');
            const { connectToDatabase, getDatabase } = require('./db');
            
            const app = express();
            app.use(express.json());
            
            let booksCollection;
            
            // Connect to database when server starts
            connectToDatabase().then(db => {
                booksCollection = db.collection('books');
                console.log('Books collection ready');
            });
            
            // GET all books
            app.get('/api/books', async (req, res) => {
                try {
                    const { genre, minPrice, maxPrice, page = 1, limit = 10 } = req.query;
                    
                    // Build query
                    const query = {};
                    
                    if (genre) {
                        query.genre = genre;
                    }
                    
                    if (minPrice || maxPrice) {
                        query.price = {};
                        if (minPrice) query.price.$gte = parseFloat(minPrice);
                        if (maxPrice) query.price.$lte = parseFloat(maxPrice);
                    }
                    
                    // Calculate pagination
                    const skip = (page - 1) * limit;
                    
                    // Execute query
                    const books = await booksCollection
                        .find(query)
                        .skip(skip)
                        .limit(parseInt(limit))
                        .toArray();
                    
                    // Get total count for pagination info
                    const total = await booksCollection.countDocuments(query);
                    
                    res.json({
                        total,
                        page: parseInt(page),
                        limit: parseInt(limit),
                        totalPages: Math.ceil(total / limit),
                        books
                    });
                } catch (error) {
                    console.error('Error fetching books:', error);
                    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Failed to fetch books' });
                }
            });
            
            // GET single book
            app.get('/api/books/:id', async (req, res) => {
                try {
                    const { id } = req.params;
                    
                    const book = await booksCollection.findOne({ 
                        _id: new require('mongodb').ObjectId(id) 
                    });
                    
                    if (!book) {
                        return res.status(404).json({ error: 'Book not found' });
                    }
                    
                    res.json(book);
                } catch (error) {
                    console.error('Error fetching book:', error);
                    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Failed to fetch book' });
                }
            });
            
            // POST create book
            app.post('/api/books', async (req, res) => {
                try {
                    const book = req.body;
                    
                    // Validate required fields
                    if (!book.title || !book.author || !book.price) {
                        return res.status(400).json({ 
                            error: 'Title, author, and price are required' 
                        });
                    }
                    
                    // Set default values
                    book.createdAt = new Date();
                    book.updatedAt = new Date();
                    book.stock = book.stock || 0;
                    
                    // Insert book
                    const result = await booksCollection.insertOne(book);
                    
                    res.status(201).json({
                        message: 'Book created successfully',
                        bookId: result.insertedId,
                        book: { ...book, _id: result.insertedId }
                    });
                } catch (error) {
                    console.error('Error creating book:', error);
                    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Failed to create book' });
                }
            });
            
            // PUT update book
            app.put('/api/books/:id', async (req, res) => {
                try {
                    const { id } = req.params;
                    const updates = req.body;
                    
                    // Add updated timestamp
                    updates.updatedAt = new Date();
                    
                    const result = await booksCollection.updateOne(
                        { _id: new require('mongodb').ObjectId(id) },
                        { $set: updates }
                    );
                    
                    if (result.matchedCount === 0) {
                        return res.status(404).json({ error: 'Book not found' });
                    }
                    
                    res.json({
                        message: 'Book updated successfully',
                        modifiedCount: result.modifiedCount
                    });
                } catch (error) {
                    console.error('Error updating book:', error);
                    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Failed to update book' });
                }
            });
            
            // DELETE book
            app.delete('/api/books/:id', async (req, res) => {
                try {
                    const { id } = req.params;
                    
                    const result = await booksCollection.deleteOne({
                        _id: new require('mongodb').ObjectId(id)
                    });
                    
                    if (result.deletedCount === 0) {
                        return res.status(404).json({ error: 'Book not found' });
                    }
                    
                    res.json({
                        message: 'Book deleted successfully',
                        deletedCount: result.deletedCount
                    });
                } catch (error) {
                    console.error('Error deleting book:', error);
                    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Failed to delete book' });
                }
            });
            
            // Start server
            const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;
            app.listen(PORT, () => {
                console.log(\`Server running on port \${PORT}\`);
            });
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>d. Using Mongoose (ODM for MongoDB)</b><br/>
    
    <b>What is Mongoose?</b>
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Mongoose</b>: An Object Data Modeling (ODM) library for MongoDB and Node.js<br/>
        <b>Benefits of Mongoose:</b>
        <ul>
            <li><b>Schema Definition</b>: Enforce structure on documents</li>
            <li><b>Validation</b>: Built-in and custom validation</li>
            <li><b>Middleware</b>: Pre/post hooks for operations</li>
            <li><b>Population</b>: Easy referencing between collections</li>
            <li><b>Type Casting</b>: Automatic type conversion</li>
            <li><b>Business Logic</b>: Instance and static methods</li>
            <li><b>Query Building</b>: Chainable query interface</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <b>Setting Up Mongoose:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            // 1. Install Mongoose
            npm install mongoose
            
            // 2. Connect to MongoDB with Mongoose
            // db.js
            const mongoose = require('mongoose');
            
            const connectToDatabase = async () => {
                try {
                    const connectionString = process.env.MONGODB_URI || 
                                           'mongodb://localhost:27017/bookstore';
                    
                    await mongoose.connect(connectionString, {
                        useNewUrlParser: true,
                        useUnifiedTopology: true,
                        useCreateIndex: true,
                        useFindAndModify: false
                    });
                    
                    console.log('Connected to MongoDB with Mongoose');
                    
                    // Connection events
                    mongoose.connection.on('error', (err) => {
                        console.error('MongoDB connection error:', err);
                    });
                    
                    mongoose.connection.on('disconnected', () => {
                        console.log('MongoDB disconnected');
                    });
                    
                    // Graceful shutdown
                    process.on('SIGINT', async () => {
                        await mongoose.connection.close();
                        console.log('MongoDB connection closed due to app termination');
                        process.exit(0);
                    });
                    
                } catch (error) {
                    console.error('Failed to connect to MongoDB:', error);
                    process.exit(1);
                }
            };
            
            module.exports = { connectToDatabase };
            
            // 3. Define Schemas and Models
            // models/Book.js
            const mongoose = require('mongoose');
            const { Schema } = mongoose;
            
            // Rating sub-schema
            const ratingSchema = new Schema({
                user: { type: String, required: true },
                score: { type: Number, min: 1, max: 5, required: true },
                comment: String,
                createdAt: { type: Date, default: Date.now }
            });
            
            // Main Book schema
            const bookSchema = new Schema({
                title: {
                    type: String,
                    required: [true, 'Title is required'],
                    trim: true,
                    minlength: [2, 'Title must be at least 2 characters'],
                    maxlength: [200, 'Title cannot exceed 200 characters']
                },
                author: {
                    type: String,
                    required: [true, 'Author is required'],
                    trim: true
                },
                genre: {
                    type: String,
                    required: true,
                    enum: ['Fiction', 'Non-Fiction', 'Science Fiction', 
                           'Fantasy', 'Mystery', 'Biography', 'Dystopian', 'Other'],
                    default: 'Other'
                },
                price: {
                    type: Number,
                    required: true,
                    min: [0, 'Price cannot be negative'],
                    validate: {
                        validator: function(value) {
                            return value <= 1000; // Custom validation
                        },
                        message: 'Price cannot exceed $1000'
                    }
                },
                stock: {
                    type: Number,
                    default: 0,
                    min: 0
                },
                publishedYear: {
                    type: Number,
                    min: [1450, 'Published year must be after 1450'],
                    max: [new Date().getFullYear(), 'Published year cannot be in the future']
                },
                isbn: {
                    type: String,
                    unique: true,
                    sparse: true // Allows null/undefined values while maintaining uniqueness
                },
                tags: [String], // Array of strings
                ratings: [ratingSchema], // Array of sub-documents
                publisher: {
                    name: String,
                    location: String
                },
                createdAt: {
                    type: Date,
                    default: Date.now,
                    immutable: true // Cannot be modified
                },
                updatedAt: {
                    type: Date,
                    default: Date.now
                }
            }, {
                timestamps: true // Automatically adds createdAt and updatedAt
            });
            
            // Indexes
            bookSchema.index({ title: 1, author: 1 }); // Compound index
            bookSchema.index({ genre: 1, price: -1 }); // Another compound index
            bookSchema.index({ title: 'text', author: 'text' }); // Text index for search
            
            // Virtual property (not stored in database)
            bookSchema.virtual('isAvailable').get(function() {
                return this.stock > 0;
            });
            
            bookSchema.virtual('formattedPrice').get(function() {
                return \`$\${this.price.toFixed(2)}\`;
            });
            
            // Instance methods (available on document instances)
            bookSchema.methods.addStock = function(quantity) {
                this.stock += quantity;
                return this.save();
            };
            
            bookSchema.methods.sell = function(quantity) {
                if (this.stock < quantity) {
                    throw new Error('Insufficient stock');
                }
                this.stock -= quantity;
                return this.save();
            };
            
            // Static methods (available on model)
            bookSchema.statics.findByGenre = function(genre) {
                return this.find({ genre });
            };
            
            bookSchema.statics.findOutOfStock = function() {
                return this.find({ stock: 0 });
            };
            
            // Query helpers (chainable)
            bookSchema.query.byAuthor = function(author) {
                return this.where({ author: new RegExp(author, 'i') });
            };
            
            bookSchema.query.cheaperThan = function(price) {
                return this.where('price').lt(price);
            };
            
            // Middleware (pre/post hooks)
            bookSchema.pre('save', function(next) {
                // Capitalize title before saving
                if (this.title) {
                    this.title = this.title
                        .split(' ')
                        .map(word => word.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + word.slice(1).toLowerCase())
                        .join(' ');
                }
                
                // Update timestamp
                this.updatedAt = Date.now();
                next();
            });
            
            bookSchema.post('save', function(doc, next) {
                console.log(\`Book saved: \${doc.title}\`);
                next();
            });
            
            // Create model
            const Book = mongoose.model('Book', bookSchema);
            
            module.exports = Book;
            
            // 4. Using the Model in Routes
            // routes/books.js
            const express = require('express');
            const router = express.Router();
            const Book = require('../models/Book');
            
            // GET all books with filtering, sorting, pagination
            router.get('/', async (req, res) => {
                try {
                    const { 
                        genre, 
                        author, 
                        minPrice, 
                        maxPrice,
                        search,
                        sort = 'title',
                        page = 1,
                        limit = 10
                    } = req.query;
                    
                    // Build query
                    let query = Book.find();
                    
                    // Apply filters
                    if (genre) {
                        query = query.where('genre', genre);
                    }
                    
                    if (author) {
                        query = query.byAuthor(author);
                    }
                    
                    if (minPrice || maxPrice) {
                        const priceFilter = {};
                        if (minPrice) priceFilter.$gte = parseFloat(minPrice);
                        if (maxPrice) priceFilter.$lte = parseFloat(maxPrice);
                        query = query.where('price', priceFilter);
                    }
                    
                    if (search) {
                        query = query.find({ $text: { $search: search } });
                    }
                    
                    // Apply sorting
                    const sortOptions = {};
                    if (sort) {
                        const sortField = sort.startsWith('-') ? sort.slice(1) : sort;
                        const sortOrder = sort.startsWith('-') ? -1 : 1;
                        sortOptions[sortField] = sortOrder;
                    }
                    query = query.sort(sortOptions);
                    
                    // Apply pagination
                    const skip = (page - 1) * limit;
                    query = query.skip(skip).limit(parseInt(limit));
                    
                    // Execute query
                    const books = await query.exec();
                    
                    // Get total count (for pagination info)
                    const countQuery = Book.find();
                    // Apply same filters to count query
                    if (genre) countQuery.where('genre', genre);
                    if (author) countQuery.byAuthor(author);
                    const total = await countQuery.countDocuments();
                    
                    res.json({
                        success: true,
                        total,
                        page: parseInt(page),
                        limit: parseInt(limit),
                        totalPages: Math.ceil(total / limit),
                        data: books
                    });
                    
                } catch (error) {
                    console.error('Error fetching books:', error);
                    res.status(500).json({ 
                        success: false, 
                        error: 'Failed to fetch books' 
                    });
                }
            });
            
            // GET single book
            router.get('/:id', async (req, res) => {
                try {
                    const book = await Book.findById(req.params.id);
                    
                    if (!book) {
                        return res.status(404).json({
                            success: false,
                            error: 'Book not found'
                        });
                    }
                    
                    res.json({
                        success: true,
                        data: book
                    });
                } catch (error) {
                    console.error('Error fetching book:', error);
                    res.status(500).json({
                        success: false,
                        error: 'Failed to fetch book'
                    });
                }
            });
            
            // POST create book
            router.post('/', async (req, res) => {
                try {
                    const book = new Book(req.body);
                    
                    // Validate and save
                    await book.save();
                    
                    res.status(201).json({
                        success: true,
                        message: 'Book created successfully',
                        data: book
                    });
                } catch (error) {
                    console.error('Error creating book:', error);
                    
                    // Handle validation errors
                    if (error.name === 'ValidationError') {
                        const errors = {};
                        Object.keys(error.errors).forEach(key => {
                            errors[key] = error.errors[key].message;
                        });
                        
                        return res.status(400).json({
                            success: false,
                            error: 'Validation failed',
                            errors
                        });
                    }
                    
                    // Handle duplicate key error
                    if (error.code === 11000) {
                        return res.status(400).json({
                            success: false,
                            error: 'Duplicate ISBN found'
                        });
                    }
                    
                    res.status(500).json({
                        success: false,
                        error: 'Failed to create book'
                    });
                }
            });
            
            // PUT update book
            router.put('/:id', async (req, res) => {
                try {
                    const book = await Book.findByIdAndUpdate(
                        req.params.id,
                        req.body,
                        { 
                            new: true, // Return updated document
                            runValidators: true // Run validation on update
                        }
                    );
                    
                    if (!book) {
                        return res.status(404).json({
                            success: false,
                            error: 'Book not found'
                        });
                    }
                    
                    res.json({
                        success: true,
                        message: 'Book updated successfully',
                        data: book
                    });
                } catch (error) {
                    console.error('Error updating book:', error);
                    
                    if (error.name === 'ValidationError') {
                        const errors = {};
                        Object.keys(error.errors).forEach(key => {
                            errors[key] = error.errors[key].message;
                        });
                        
                        return res.status(400).json({
                            success: false,
                            error: 'Validation failed',
                            errors
                        });
                    }
                    
                    res.status(500).json({
                        success: false,
                        error: 'Failed to update book'
                    });
                }
            });
            
            // DELETE book
            router.delete('/:id', async (req, res) => {
                try {
                    const book = await Book.findByIdAndDelete(req.params.id);
                    
                    if (!book) {
                        return res.status(404).json({
                            success: false,
                            error: 'Book not found'
                        });
                    }
                    
                    res.json({
                        success: true,
                        message: 'Book deleted successfully'
                    });
                } catch (error) {
                    console.error('Error deleting book:', error);
                    res.status(500).json({
                        success: false,
                        error: 'Failed to delete book'
                    });
                }
            });
            
            // Custom endpoint: Add stock
            router.post('/:id/stock/add', async (req, res) => {
                try {
                    const { quantity } = req.body;
                    const book = await Book.findById(req.params.id);
                    
                    if (!book) {
                        return res.status(404).json({
                            success: false,
                            error: 'Book not found'
                        });
                    }
                    
                    await book.addStock(parseInt(quantity));
                    
                    res.json({
                        success: true,
                        message: \`Added \${quantity} to stock\`,
                        data: book
                    });
                } catch (error) {
                    console.error('Error adding stock:', error);
                    res.status(500).json({
                        success: false,
                        error: 'Failed to add stock'
                    });
                }
            });
            
            module.exports = router;
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>e. Data Modeling in MongoDB</b><br/>
    
    <b>Design Patterns for Document Databases:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>1. Embedded Documents Pattern</b>: Store related data in a single document
        <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 10px; margin: 5px 0; border-radius: 3px;">
            <pre>
                // Good for: One-to-few relationships, data accessed together
                {
                    _id: 1,
                    title: "Blog Post",
                    content: "...",
                    comments: [  // Embedded comments
                        { user: "Alice", text: "Great post!", date: "2024-01-20" },
                        { user: "Bob", text: "Thanks for sharing", date: "2024-01-21" }
                    ]
                }
            </pre>
        </div>
        
        <b>2. Referenced Documents Pattern</b>: Store references to other documents
        <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 10px; margin: 5px 0; border-radius: 3px;">
            <pre>
                // Good for: One-to-many, many-to-many relationships
                // Order document
                {
                    _id: 101,
                    userId: 1,  // Reference to user
                    items: [
                        { productId: 201, quantity: 2 },  // Reference to product
                        { productId: 202, quantity: 1 }
                    ]
                }
                
                // Then use Mongoose populate() to get full documents
                Order.findById(101).populate('userId').populate('items.productId');
            </pre>
        </div>
        
        <b>3. Extended Reference Pattern</b>: Store frequently accessed fields + reference
        <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 10px; margin: 5px 0; border-radius: 3px;">
            <pre>
                // Good for: Reducing joins while maintaining relationships
                {
                    _id: 101,
                    userId: 1,
                    userName: "John Doe",  // Denormalized for quick access
                    userEmail: "john@example.com",
                    items: [
                        {
                            productId: 201,
                            productName: "Laptop",  // Denormalized
                            price: 999.99,
                            quantity: 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            </pre>
        </div>
        
        <b>4. Bucket Pattern</b>: Group related data into buckets
        <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 10px; margin: 5px 0; border-radius: 3px;">
            <pre>
                // Good for: Time-series data, IoT sensor readings
                {
                    sensorId: "temp-sensor-1",
                    month: "2024-01",
                    readings: [  // Hourly readings for the month
                        { timestamp: "2024-01-01T00:00:00Z", value: 22.5 },
                        { timestamp: "2024-01-01T01:00:00Z", value: 22.3 },
                        // ... up to 744 readings (31 days * 24 hours)
                    ]
                }
            </pre>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <b>Relationship Patterns:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            // One-to-One: Embed or reference
            // Option 1: Embed (if always accessed together)
            {
                _id: 1,
                name: "John",
                address: {  // Embedded
                    street: "123 Main St",
                    city: "New York"
                }
            }
            
            // Option 2: Reference (if large or optional)
            {
                _id: 1,
                name: "John",
                addressId: 101  // Reference to address document
            }
            
            // One-to-Few: Usually embed
            {
                _id: 1,
                title: "Blog Post",
                comments: [  // Embedded array
                    { user: "Alice", text: "Great!" },
                    { user: "Bob", text: "Thanks!" }
                ]
            }
            
            // One-to-Many: Usually reference
            // User document
            {
                _id: 1,
                name: "John",
                email: "john@example.com"
            }
            
            // Post documents (many)
            { _id: 101, userId: 1, title: "First Post", content: "..." }
            { _id: 102, userId: 1, title: "Second Post", content: "..." }
            
            // Many-to-Many: Array of references
            // Student document
            {
                _id: 1,
                name: "Alice",
                courses: [101, 102, 103]  // References to courses
            }
            
            // Course document
            {
                _id: 101,
                title: "Math 101",
                students: [1, 2, 3]  // References to students
            }
            
            // With Mongoose populate:
            Student.findById(1).populate('courses');
            Course.findById(101).populate('students');
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <h3>Hands-On Exercise: E-commerce Database Design</h3>
    
    <b>Task:</b> Design and implement a MongoDB database for an e-commerce application<br/><br/>
    
    <b>Requirements:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Entities to Model:</b>
        1. <b>User</b>: Customers with authentication details
        2. <b>Product</b>: Items for sale with variants
        3. <b>Category</b>: Product categories and subcategories
        4. <b>Order</b>: Customer purchases
        5. <b>Review</b>: Product reviews and ratings
        
        <b>Relationships:</b>
        - One User can have many Orders
        - One Order can have many Products
        - One Product belongs to one or more Categories
        - One Product can have many Reviews
        - One User can write many Reviews
        
        <b>Features to Implement:</b>
        1. Product search with filters (category, price range, rating)
        2. Shopping cart functionality
        3. Order history for users
        4. Product recommendations
        5. Inventory management
        6. Sales analytics
    </div>
    
    <b>Schema Design Example:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            // models/User.js
            const userSchema = new Schema({
                email: { type: String, required: true, unique: true },
                password: { type: String, required: true },
                firstName: String,
                lastName: String,
                address: {
                    street: String,
                    city: String,
                    state: String,
                    zipCode: String,
                    country: String
                },
                phone: String,
                cart: [{
                    productId: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Product' },
                    quantity: { type: Number, default: 1 },
                    variant: String  // Size, color, etc.
                }],
                wishlist: [{ type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Product' }],
                orders: [{ type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Order' }],
                createdAt: { type: Date, default: Date.now }
            });
            
            // models/Product.js
            const variantSchema = new Schema({
                name: String,  // e.g., "Size", "Color"
                options: [String]  // e.g., ["Small", "Medium", "Large"]
            });
            
            const productSchema = new Schema({
                name: { type: String, required: true },
                description: String,
                sku: { type: String, unique: true },
                price: { type: Number, required: true, min: 0 },
                compareAtPrice: Number,  // Original price for discounts
                cost: Number,  // Cost to business
                category: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Category' },
                subcategory: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Category' },
                tags: [String],
                variants: [variantSchema],
                inventory: {
                    total: { type: Number, default: 0 },
                    available: { type: Number, default: 0 },
                    reserved: { type: Number, default: 0 }
                },
                images: [String],  // URLs to product images
                specifications: Map,  // Key-value pairs for specifications
                rating: {
                    average: { type: Number, default: 0, min: 0, max: 5 },
                    count: { type: Number, default: 0 }
                },
                isActive: { type: Boolean, default: true },
                createdAt: { type: Date, default: Date.now },
                updatedAt: { type: Date, default: Date.now }
            });
            
            // models/Category.js
            const categorySchema = new Schema({
                name: { type: String, required: true },
                slug: { type: String, required: true, unique: true },
                description: String,
                parent: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Category' },  // For hierarchy
                image: String,
                isActive: { type: Boolean, default: true }
            });
            
            // models/Order.js
            const orderItemSchema = new Schema({
                productId: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Product' },
                name: String,  // Denormalized for history
                price: Number,  // Price at time of purchase
                quantity: Number,
                variant: String,
                total: Number  // price * quantity
            });
            
            const orderSchema = new Schema({
                orderNumber: { type: String, unique: true },
                userId: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'User' },
                items: [orderItemSchema],
                subtotal: Number,
                tax: Number,
                shipping: Number,
                discount: Number,
                total: Number,
                status: {
                    type: String,
                    enum: ['pending', 'processing', 'shipped', 'delivered', 'cancelled'],
                    default: 'pending'
                },
                shippingAddress: {
                    street: String,
                    city: String,
                    state: String,
                    zipCode: String,
                    country: String
                },
                billingAddress: {
                    street: String,
                    city: String,
                    state: String,
                    zipCode: String,
                    country: String
                },
                payment: {
                    method: String,
                    transactionId: String,
                    status: String
                },
                notes: String,
                createdAt: { type: Date, default: Date.now },
                updatedAt: { type: Date, default: Date.now }
            });
            
            // Generate order number before saving
            orderSchema.pre('save', async function(next) {
                if (!this.orderNumber) {
                    const count = await this.constructor.countDocuments();
                    this.orderNumber = \`ORD-\${String(count + 1).padStart(6, '0')}\`;
                }
                next();
            });
            
            // models/Review.js
            const reviewSchema = new Schema({
                productId: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'Product' },
                userId: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'User' },
                rating: { type: Number, required: true, min: 1, max: 5 },
                title: String,
                comment: String,
                images: [String],
                isVerifiedPurchase: { type: Boolean, default: false },
                helpful: { type: Number, default: 0 },
                notHelpful: { type: Number, default: 0 },
                createdAt: { type: Date, default: Date.now }
            });
            
            // Update product rating when review is saved
            reviewSchema.post('save', async function() {
                const Review = this.constructor;
                const Product = require('./Product');
                
                const stats = await Review.aggregate([
                    { $match: { productId: this.productId } },
                    { $group: {
                        _id: '$productId',
                        averageRating: { $avg: '$rating' },
                        reviewCount: { $sum: 1 }
                    }}
                ]);
                
                if (stats.length > 0) {
                    await Product.findByIdAndUpdate(this.productId, {
                        'rating.average': stats[0].averageRating,
                        'rating.count': stats[0].reviewCount
                    });
                }
            });
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Complex Query Examples:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            // 1. Product search with multiple filters
            const searchProducts = async (filters) => {
                const {
                    query,
                    category,
                    minPrice,
                    maxPrice,
                    minRating,
                    inStock,
                    sortBy = 'name',
                    sortOrder = 'asc',
                    page = 1,
                    limit = 20
                } = filters;
                
                const skip = (page - 1) * limit;
                
                // Build search query
                const searchQuery = {};
                
                if (query) {
                    searchQuery.$text = { $search: query };
                }
                
                if (category) {
                    searchQuery.category = category;
                }
                
                if (minPrice !== undefined || maxPrice !== undefined) {
                    searchQuery.price = {};
                    if (minPrice !== undefined) searchQuery.price.$gte = minPrice;
                    if (maxPrice !== undefined) searchQuery.price.$lte = maxPrice;
                }
                
                if (minRating !== undefined) {
                    searchQuery['rating.average'] = { $gte: minRating };
                }
                
                if (inStock !== undefined) {
                    if (inStock) {
                        searchQuery['inventory.available'] = { $gt: 0 };
                    } else {
                        searchQuery['inventory.available'] = { $eq: 0 };
                    }
                }
                
                // Determine sort
                const sortOptions = {};
                if (sortBy === 'price') {
                    sortOptions.price = sortOrder === 'desc' ? -1 : 1;
                } else if (sortBy === 'rating') {
                    sortOptions['rating.average'] = sortOrder === 'desc' ? -1 : 1;
                } else if (sortBy === 'name') {
                    sortOptions.name = sortOrder === 'desc' ? -1 : 1;
                }
                
                // Execute query
                const products = await Product.find(searchQuery)
                    .populate('category', 'name slug')
                    .sort(sortOptions)
                    .skip(skip)
                    .limit(limit)
                    .exec();
                
                const total = await Product.countDocuments(searchQuery);
                
                return {
                    products,
                    total,
                    page,
                    totalPages: Math.ceil(total / limit),
                    hasMore: page * limit < total
                };
            };
            
            // 2. Get user's order history with populated product details
            const getOrderHistory = async (userId, page = 1, limit = 10) => {
                const skip = (page - 1) * limit;
                
                const orders = await Order.find({ userId })
                    .populate({
                        path: 'items.productId',
                        select: 'name images',
                        model: 'Product'
                    })
                    .sort({ createdAt: -1 })
                    .skip(skip)
                    .limit(limit)
                    .exec();
                
                const total = await Order.countDocuments({ userId });
                
                return {
                    orders,
                    total,
                    page,
                    totalPages: Math.ceil(total / limit)
                };
            };
            
            // 3. Sales analytics aggregation
            const getSalesAnalytics = async (startDate, endDate) => {
                const analytics = await Order.aggregate([
                    {
                        $match: {
                            createdAt: {
                                $gte: new Date(startDate),
                                $lte: new Date(endDate)
                            },
                            status: { $ne: 'cancelled' }
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        $unwind: '$items'
                    },
                    {
                        $lookup: {
                            from: 'products',
                            localField: 'items.productId',
                            foreignField: '_id',
                            as: 'productDetails'
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        $unwind: '$productDetails'
                    },
                    {
                        $group: {
                            _id: {
                                productId: '$items.productId',
                                productName: '$productDetails.name',
                                category: '$productDetails.category'
                            },
                            totalQuantity: { $sum: '$items.quantity' },
                            totalRevenue: { $sum: { $multiply: ['$items.price', '$items.quantity'] } },
                            orderCount: { $sum: 1 }
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        $group: {
                            _id: '$_id.category',
                            products: {
                                $push: {
                                    productId: '$_id.productId',
                                    productName: '$_id.productName',
                                    totalQuantity: '$totalQuantity',
                                    totalRevenue: '$totalRevenue',
                                    orderCount: '$orderCount'
                                }
                            },
                            categoryRevenue: { $sum: '$totalRevenue' },
                            categoryQuantity: { $sum: '$totalQuantity' }
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        $sort: { categoryRevenue: -1 }
                    }
                ]);
                
                return analytics;
            };
            
            // 4. Get product recommendations based on user's purchase history
            const getProductRecommendations = async (userId) => {
                // Get products user has purchased
                const userOrders = await Order.find({ userId })
                    .populate('items.productId');
                
                const purchasedProductIds = [];
                userOrders.forEach(order => {
                    order.items.forEach(item => {
                        if (item.productId) {
                            purchasedProductIds.push(item.productId._id);
                        }
                    });
                });
                
                if (purchasedProductIds.length === 0) {
                    // If no purchase history, return popular products
                    return await Product.find()
                        .sort({ 'rating.average': -1, 'rating.count': -1 })
                        .limit(10)
                        .exec();
                }
                
                // Find other users who bought the same products
                const similarUsers = await Order.aggregate([
                    {
                        $match: {
                            'items.productId': { $in: purchasedProductIds },
                            userId: { $ne: new mongoose.Types.ObjectId(userId) }
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        $group: {
                            _id: '$userId',
                            commonProducts: { $sum: 1 }
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        $sort: { commonProducts: -1 }
                    },
                    {
                        $limit: 10
                    }
                ]);
                
                const similarUserIds = similarUsers.map(user => user._id);
                
                // Get products bought by similar users that current user hasn't bought
                const recommendedProducts = await Order.aggregate([
                    {
                        $match: {
                            userId: { $in: similarUserIds }
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        $unwind: '$items'
                    },
                    {
                        $match: {
                            'items.productId': { $nin: purchasedProductIds }
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        $group: {
                            _id: '$items.productId',
                            purchaseCount: { $sum: 1 }
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        $sort: { purchaseCount: -1 }
                    },
                    {
                        $limit: 10
                    },
                    {
                        $lookup: {
                            from: 'products',
                            localField: '_id',
                            foreignField: '_id',
                            as: 'productDetails'
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        $unwind: '$productDetails'
                    },
                    {
                        $replaceRoot: {
                            newRoot: {
                                $mergeObjects: [
                                    { purchaseCount: '$purchaseCount' },
                                    '$productDetails'
                                ]
                            }
                        }
                    }
                ]);
                
                return recommendedProducts;
            };
        </pre>
    </div>
    
