    ‚Ä¢ <a href="https://haveibeenpwned.com/" target="_blank">Have I Been Pwned (Password checker)</a></p>
</div>`
            },
            "10-4": {
                icon: "fa-rocket",
                title: "API Development & Best Practices",
                html: `<h1>Week 10, Day 4: API Development & Best Practices</h1>
    <p>Today we'll learn how to build robust, scalable, and maintainable APIs following industry best practices.</p>
    
    <div class="analogy-box">
        <b>Analogy: Restaurant Menu & Service Standards üçΩÔ∏è</b><br/>
        
       RESTful Design: Well-organized menu with clear categories<br/>
       API Documentation: Detailed menu with descriptions and prices<br/>
       Versioning: Updated menu versions for seasonal changes<br/>
       Rate Limiting: Reservation system to prevent overcrowding<br/>
       Caching: Pre-prepared dishes for faster service<br/>
       Error Handling: Clear explanations when dishes aren't available<br/>
       Validation: Checking orders for correctness before cooking<br/>
       Testing: Quality control in the kitchen
    </div>

    <h3>Key Topics</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>RESTful API design principles</li>
        <li>API versioning strategies</li>
        <li>Comprehensive error handling</li>
        <li>Input validation and sanitization</li>
        <li>API documentation (OpenAPI/Swagger)</li>
        <li>Rate limiting and throttling</li>
        <li>Caching strategies</li>
        <li>API testing and monitoring</li>
        <li>Performance optimization</li>
        <li>Security best practices</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>In-Depth Explanation</h3>
    
    <b>a. RESTful API Design Principles</b><br/>
    
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>REST (REpresentational State Transfer)</b>: Architectural style for designing networked applications<br/>
        
        <b>REST Constraints:</b>
        <ul>
            <li><b>Client-Server</b>: Separation of concerns</li>
            <li><b>Stateless</b>: Each request contains all necessary information</li>
            <li><b>Cacheable</b>: Responses must define if they're cacheable</li>
            <li><b>Uniform Interface</b>: Consistent way of interacting</li>
            <li><b>Layered System</b>: Intermediary servers can be inserted</li>
            <li><b>Code on Demand (optional)</b>: Servers can extend client functionality</li>
        </ul>
        
        <b>RESTful Best Practices:</b>
        <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 10px;">
            <tr style="background-color: #4a86e8; color: white;">
                <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Aspect</th>
                <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Best Practice</th>
                <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Example</th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Nouns not Verbs</b></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Use resource names, not actions</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">/users not /getUsers</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Plural Nouns</b></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Use plural for collections</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">/users not /user</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>HTTP Methods</b></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Use appropriate HTTP verbs</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Nested Resources</b></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Show relationships in URLs</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">/users/123/posts</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Filter/Sort/Paginate</b></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Use query parameters</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">/users?page=2&limit=10&sort=name</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Versioning</b></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Include version in URL or header</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">/api/v1/users</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Status Codes</b></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Use appropriate HTTP status codes</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">200, 201, 400, 404, 500</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;"><b>Consistent Response</b></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Standard response format</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">{success, data, error, message}</td>
            </tr>
        </table>
    </div>
    
    <b>RESTful API Example Structure:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            // Resource: Users<br/>
            GET    /api/v1/users           # List users<br/>
            POST   /api/v1/users           # Create user<br/>
            GET    /api/v1/users/:id       # Get user<br/>
            PUT    /api/v1/users/:id       # Update entire user<br/>
            PATCH  /api/v1/users/:id       # Update partial user<br/>
            DELETE /api/v1/users/:id       # Delete user<br/>
            <br/>
            // Nested resources<br/>
            GET    /api/v1/users/:id/posts          # Get user's posts<br/>
            POST   /api/v1/users/:id/posts          # Create post for user<br/>
            GET    /api/v1/users/:id/posts/:postId  # Get specific post<br/>
            <br/>
            {<br/>
                "success": true,<br/>
                "data": { "users": [...] }<br/>
            }
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <hr/>
    
    <b>b. API Versioning Strategies</b><br/>
    
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            // Header Versioning Implementation<br/>
            const versionMiddleware = (req, res, next) => {<br/>
                const acceptHeader = req.headers.accept || '';<br/>
                const versionMatch = acceptHeader.match(/application\\/vnd\\.api\\.v(\\d+)\\+json/);<br/>
                <br/>
                if (versionMatch) {<br/>
                    req.apiVersion = parseInt(versionMatch[1]);<br/>
                } else {<br/>
                    req.apiVersion = 1;<br/>
                }<br/>
                next();<br/>
            };<br/>
            <br/>
            // Example response using interpolation inside the template<br/>
            res.status(400).json({<br/>
                error: \`Unsupported API version: \${req.apiVersion}\`<br/>
            });<br/>
            <br/>
            // Example of nested interpolation<br/>
            links: {<br/>
                self: \`/api/v2/users/\${user._id}\`<br/>
            }
        </pre>
    </div>

    <hr/>

    <b>c. Comprehensive Error Handling</b><br/>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            class AppError extends Error {<br/>
                constructor(message, statusCode) {<br/>
                    super(message);<br/>
                    this.statusCode = statusCode;<br/>
                    this.status = \`\${statusCode}\`.startsWith('4') ? 'fail' : 'error';<br/>
                    Error.captureStackTrace(this, this.constructor);<br/>
                }<br/>
            }<br/>
            <br/>
            // MongoDB duplicate key error<br/>
            if (err.code === 11000) {<br/>
                const field = Object.keys(err.keyValue)[0];<br/>
                const value = err.keyValue[field];<br/>
                err = new ValidationError(\`Duplicate field value: \${field} = \${value}\`);<br/>
            }
        </pre>
    </div>`
            },

            "11-1": {
                icon: "fa-database",
                title: "Introduction to Relational Databases",
                html: `<h1>Week 11, Day 1: Introduction to Relational Databases</h1>
    <p>Today we begin Level 3 by diving into databases! We'll learn how data is organized, stored, and retrieved in relational databases using MySQL.</p>

    <div class="analogy-box">
        <b>Analogy: The Digital Filing Cabinet üìÅ</b><br/>
        
        Database: A well-organized filing cabinet<br/>
        Table: A file folder for specific types of documents<br/>
        Row: A single document in the folder<br/>
        Column: A specific piece of information on the document<br/>
        Primary Key: A unique document ID number<br/>
        Foreign Key: A reference to another document<br/>
        SQL: The language for talking to the filing clerk<br/>
        Index: An alphabetical index for quick finding
    </div>

    <h3>What is a Relational Database?</h3>

    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 20px; margin: 15px 0; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #4A90E2;">
        <h4>üìä Database vs. Spreadsheet Thinking</h4>
        
        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
            <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
                <h5 style="color: #e74c3c; margin-top: 0;">‚ùå Spreadsheet (Excel)</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>Single table/sheet</li>
                    <li>Data duplication common</li>
                    <li>Limited data validation</li>
                    <li>Manual relationships</li>
                    <li>No built-in security</li>
                    <li>Single-user focus</li>
                    <li>File-based storage</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
                <h5 style="color: #27ae60; margin-top: 0;">‚úÖ Database (MySQL)</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>Multiple related tables</li>
                    <li>Minimal duplication</li>
                    <li>Strong data validation</li>
                    <li>Automatic relationships</li>
                    <li>User permissions system</li>
                    <li>Multi-user concurrent access</li>
                    <li>Server-based storage</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h3>Database Structure & Terminology</h3>

    <b>The Hierarchy of Database Organization:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
    <pre>
    DATABASE (finance_app)
        ‚îÇ
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ TABLE (users)
        ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ COLUMN: user_id (INT, Primary Key)
        ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ COLUMN: username (VARCHAR)
        ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ COLUMN: email (VARCHAR)
        ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ COLUMN: created_at (DATETIME)
        ‚îÇ
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ TABLE (transactions)
        ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ COLUMN: transaction_id (INT, Primary Key)
        ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ COLUMN: user_id (INT, Foreign Key ‚Üí users.user_id)
        ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ COLUMN: amount (DECIMAL)
        ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ COLUMN: type (ENUM: 'income', 'expense')
        ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ COLUMN: date (DATE)
        ‚îÇ
        ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ TABLE (categories)
            ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ COLUMN: category_id (INT, Primary Key)
            ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ COLUMN: name (VARCHAR)
            ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ COLUMN: user_id (INT, Foreign Key ‚Üí users.user_id)
    </pre>
    </div>

    <h3>Setting Up MySQL Environment</h3>

    <b>Option 1: XAMPP/WAMP/MAMP (Local Development)</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
    <pre>
    // Installation Steps:
    1. Download XAMPP from https://www.apachefriends.org/
    2. Install with default settings
    3. Open XAMPP Control Panel
    4. Start Apache and MySQL services
    5. Open browser to http://localhost/phpmyadmin
    6. Default credentials:
    - Username: root
    - Password: (leave empty)

    // Verify Installation:
    1. Create test database:
    CREATE DATABASE test_db;
    
    2. Create test table:
    USE test_db;
    CREATE TABLE users (
        id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
        name VARCHAR(50),
        email VARCHAR(100)
    );

    3. Insert test data:
    INSERT INTO users (name, email) 
    VALUES ('John Doe', 'john@example.com');

    4. Query data:
    SELECT * FROM users;
    </pre>
    </div>

    <b>Option 2: Online MySQL Sandbox (No Installation Required)</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
    <pre>
    // Free Online MySQL Sandboxes:
    1. SQL Fiddle: http://sqlfiddle.com/
    - No registration required
    - Supports MySQL 5.6, 8.0
    - Shareable links for collaboration

    2. DB Fiddle: https://www.db-fiddle.com/
    - MySQL 5.7, 8.0
    - PostgreSQL, SQLite options
    - Schema + data persistence

    3. phpMyAdmin Demo: https://demo.phpmyadmin.net/
    - Full phpMyAdmin interface
    - Temporary databases (24h)
    - No installation needed

    // Using SQL Fiddle:
    1. Go to http://sqlfiddle.com/
    2. Left panel (Schema): Write CREATE statements
    3. Right panel (SQL): Write SELECT/INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE
    4. Click "Build Schema" then "Run SQL"
    5. Share your fiddle link with others
    </pre>
    </div>

    <h3>Understanding Data Types</h3>

    <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
    <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 15px 0;">
        <thead>
            <tr style="background-color: #4A90E2; color: white;">
                <th style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #ddd; text-align: left;">Category</th>
                <th style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #ddd; text-align: left;">Type</th>
                <th style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #ddd; text-align: left;">Description</th>
                <th style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #ddd; text-align: left;">Example</th>
                <th style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #ddd; text-align: left;">Storage</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;" rowspan="3"><b>Numeric</b></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">INT</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Whole numbers</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">-2147483648 to 2147483647</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">4 bytes</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">DECIMAL(10,2)</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Exact decimal numbers</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">12345678.99</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Varies</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">FLOAT</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Approximate decimals</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">3.14159</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">4 bytes</td>
            </tr>
            
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;" rowspan="4"><b>String</b></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">VARCHAR(255)</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Variable length text</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">'Hello World'</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Length + 1 byte</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">CHAR(10)</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Fixed length text</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">'USD' (padded)</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Fixed length</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">TEXT</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Large text</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Long descriptions</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Varies</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">ENUM('Y','N')</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Predefined list</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">'Y' or 'N' only</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">1-2 bytes</td>
            </tr>
            
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;" rowspan="3"><b>Date/Time</b></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">DATE</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Date only</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">'2024-01-20'</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">3 bytes</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">DATETIME</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Date + Time</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">'2024-01-20 14:30:00'</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">8 bytes</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">TIMESTAMP</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Auto-updating time</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">'2024-01-20 14:30:00'</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">4 bytes</td>
            </tr>
            
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;" rowspan="2"><b>Binary</b></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">BLOB</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Binary large object</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Images, PDFs</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Varies</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">BOOLEAN</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">True/False</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">TRUE, FALSE, 1, 0</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">1 byte</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
    </div>

    <h3>Creating Your First Database</h3>

    <b>Complete Finance App Database Schema:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
    <pre>
    -- Create Database
    CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS finance_app;
    USE finance_app;

    -- Users Table (Master Table)
    CREATE TABLE users (
        user_id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
        username VARCHAR(50) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
        email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
        password_hash VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
        full_name VARCHAR(100),
        monthly_budget DECIMAL(10,2) DEFAULT 3000.00,
        currency VARCHAR(3) DEFAULT 'USD',
        created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
        updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
        INDEX idx_username (username),
        INDEX idx_email (email)
    );

    -- Categories Table
    CREATE TABLE categories (
        category_id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
        user_id INT NOT NULL,
        name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
        type ENUM('income', 'expense') NOT NULL,
        color VARCHAR(7) DEFAULT '#4A90E2',
        icon VARCHAR(50) DEFAULT 'fas fa-tag',
        is_default BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,
        created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
        FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
        UNIQUE KEY unique_user_category (user_id, name, type),
        INDEX idx_user_id (user_id),
        INDEX idx_type (type)
    );

    -- Transactions Table (Core Table)
    CREATE TABLE transactions (
        transaction_id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
        user_id INT NOT NULL,
        category_id INT NOT NULL,
        amount DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
        type ENUM('income', 'expense') NOT NULL,
        description VARCHAR(255),
        transaction_date DATE NOT NULL,
        created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
        updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
        FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
        FOREIGN KEY (category_id) REFERENCES categories(category_id) ON DELETE RESTRICT,
        INDEX idx_user_id (user_id),
        INDEX idx_category_id (category_id),
        INDEX idx_transaction_date (transaction_date),
        INDEX idx_type (type),
        INDEX idx_user_date (user_id, transaction_date)
    );

    -- Savings Goals Table
    CREATE TABLE savings_goals (
        goal_id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
        user_id INT NOT NULL,
        goal_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
        target_amount DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
        current_amount DECIMAL(10,2) DEFAULT 0.00,
        deadline DATE,
        is_completed BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,
        created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
        updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
        FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
        INDEX idx_user_id (user_id),
        INDEX idx_completed (is_completed)
    );

    -- Budgets Table (Monthly)
    CREATE TABLE budgets (
        budget_id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
        user_id INT NOT NULL,
        category_id INT NOT NULL,
        month_year DATE NOT NULL, -- First day of month
        amount DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
        created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
        FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
        FOREIGN KEY (category_id) REFERENCES categories(category_id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
        UNIQUE KEY unique_user_category_month (user_id, category_id, month_year),
        INDEX idx_user_month (user_id, month_year)
    );

    -- Recurring Transactions
    CREATE TABLE recurring_transactions (
        recurring_id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
        user_id INT NOT NULL,
        category_id INT NOT NULL,
        amount DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
        type ENUM('income', 'expense') NOT NULL,
        description VARCHAR(255),
        frequency ENUM('daily', 'weekly', 'monthly', 'yearly') NOT NULL,
        start_date DATE NOT NULL,
        end_date DATE,
        last_processed DATE,
        is_active BOOLEAN DEFAULT TRUE,
        created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
        FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
        FOREIGN KEY (category_id) REFERENCES categories(category_id) ON DELETE RESTRICT,
        INDEX idx_user_active (user_id, is_active),
        INDEX idx_next_processing (last_processed, frequency)
    );
    </pre>
