    <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; margin: 20px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <h3>üí° Database Design Best Practices:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><b>Use Meaningful Names:</b> Table and column names should be clear (users, not tbl_usr)</li>
            <li><b>Choose Appropriate Data Types:</b> Don't use VARCHAR for dates or INT for booleans</li>
            <li><b>Always Have a Primary Key:</b> Every table should have a unique identifier</li>
            <li><b>Use Foreign Keys for Relationships:</b> Maintain referential integrity</li>
            <li><b>Add Indexes Strategically:</b> Index columns used in WHERE, JOIN, and ORDER BY</li>
            <li><b>Normalize Your Data:</b> Eliminate redundancy, but don't over-normalize</li>
            <li><b>Add Timestamps:</b> Include created_at and updated_at for auditing</li>
            <li><b>Document Your Schema:</b> Keep an updated ERD and data dictionary</li>
            <li><b>Test with Realistic Data:</b> Your design should handle real-world data volumes</li>
            <li><b>Plan for Growth:</b> Consider how your schema will scale</li>
        </ul>
