                </ul>

                3. <b>UPDATE Practice (20 minutes):</b>
                <ul>
                    <li>Increase all budgets by 5%</li>
                    <li>Update a user's email address</li>
                    <li>Mark a savings goal as completed</li>
                    <li>Correct transaction amounts that were entered incorrectly</li>
                    <li>Update transaction descriptions to add a prefix</li>
                </ul>

                4. <b>DELETE Practice (15 minutes):</b>
                <ul>
                    <li>Remove test transactions from a specific date</li>
                    <li>Delete a user account (cascade will remove related data)</li>
                    <li>Remove duplicate categories</li>
                    <li>Clean up old sessions or temporary data</li>
                    <li>Practice safe delete with LIMIT</li>
                </ul>

                5. <b>Combined Operations (15 minutes):</b>
                <ul>
                    <li>Find and update transactions that match a pattern</li>
                    <li>Insert data based on existing data (subquery insert)</li>
                    <li>Update based on joined tables</li>
                    <li>Delete with complex conditions</li>
                </ul>

                6. <b>Error Handling Practice:</b>
                <ul>
                    <li>Try to insert duplicate data (observe error)</li>
                    <li>Update with invalid WHERE clause (affects multiple rows)</li>
                    <li>Delete without WHERE clause (SAFETY FIRST - use transactions!)</li>
                    <li>Insert data with wrong data types</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h3>SQL Best Practices & Safety</h3>

            <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 20px 0; border-radius: 5px; border-left: 5px solid #e74c3c;">
                <h4 style="color: #e74c3c; margin-top: 0;">‚ö†Ô∏è CRITICAL SAFETY RULES ‚ö†Ô∏è</h4>
                
                <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 15px; margin-top: 10px;">
                    <div>
                        <h5 style="color: #c0392b;">‚ùå NEVER DO THIS:</h5>
                        <code style="display: block; background: #f8d7da; padding: 10px; border-radius: 3px; margin: 5px 0; color: #721c24;">
            UPDATE users SET password = 'newpass';<br/>
            DELETE FROM transactions;<br/>
            DROP TABLE users;
                        </pre>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div>
                        <h5 style="color: #27ae60;">‚úÖ ALWAYS DO THIS:</h5>
                        <code style="display: block; background: #d4edda; padding: 10px; border-radius: 3px; margin: 5px 0; color: #155724;">
            UPDATE users SET password = 'newpass' WHERE user_id = 1;<br/>
            DELETE FROM transactions WHERE date < '2020-01-01';<br/>
            -- Test with SELECT first!<br/>
            SELECT * FROM transactions WHERE date < '2020-01-01';
                        </pre>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <b>Essential Safety Practices:</b>
            <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
            <pre>
            -- 1. ALWAYS use WHERE with UPDATE and DELETE
            -- Bad:
            UPDATE products SET price = price * 1.1;
            -- Good:
            UPDATE products SET price = price * 1.1 WHERE category = 'electronics';

            -- 2. Test with SELECT first
            -- Before DELETE:
            SELECT * FROM transactions WHERE transaction_date < '2023-01-01';
            -- Then DELETE:
            DELETE FROM transactions WHERE transaction_date < '2023-01-01';

            -- 3. Use transactions for multiple operations
            START TRANSACTION;
                UPDATE accounts SET balance = balance - 100 WHERE account_id = 1;
                UPDATE accounts SET balance = balance + 100 WHERE account_id = 2;
                INSERT INTO transfers (from_account, to_account, amount) VALUES (1, 2, 100);
            COMMIT;
            -- If something goes wrong: ROLLBACK;

            -- 4. Use LIMIT with UPDATE/DELETE on large tables
            UPDATE large_table SET status = 'processed' WHERE status = 'pending' LIMIT 1000;

            -- 5. Backup before major operations
            CREATE TABLE users_backup_20240120 AS SELECT * FROM users;

            -- 6. Use EXPLAIN to understand query performance
            EXPLAIN SELECT * FROM transactions WHERE user_id = 1;

            -- 7. Validate input data
            INSERT INTO users (username, email) 
            VALUES ('valid_username', 'valid@email.com');  -- Sanitized input

            -- 8. Use prepared statements (in application code)
            -- PHP example: $stmt = $pdo->prepare("SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ?");
            --              $stmt->execute([$userId]);

            -- 9. Regular backups
            -- Daily: mysqldump -u root -p finance_app > backup_$(date +%Y%m%d).sql

            -- 10. Monitor and log destructive operations
            CREATE TABLE audit_log (
                id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
                operation VARCHAR(20),
                table_name VARCHAR(50),
                affected_rows INT,
                executed_by VARCHAR(50),
                executed_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
            );

            -- Trigger example for logging
            CREATE TRIGGER after_user_delete
            AFTER DELETE ON users
            FOR EACH ROW
            INSERT INTO audit_log (operation, table_name, affected_rows, executed_by)
            VALUES ('DELETE', 'users', 1, CURRENT_USER());
            </pre>
            </div>

            <h3>Homework Assignment: SQL Mastery</h3>

            <div style="background-color: #fff0e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
                <b>Task 1: Write 20 SQL Queries</b>
                <p>Create SQL queries that demonstrate your understanding:</p>
                
                <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 15px; margin: 15px 0;">
