                        </ol>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div>
                        <h5 style="margin-top: 0;">Data Modification (5):</h5>
                        <ol style="font-size: 14px;" start="16">
                            <li>Bulk update for currency conversion</li>
                            <li>Archive old transactions</li>
                            <li>Fix data quality issues</li>
                            <li>Generate monthly reports</li>
                            <li>Clean up orphaned records</li>
                        </ol>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <b>Task 2: Performance Analysis</b>
                <ul>
                    <li>Use EXPLAIN on your queries</li>
                    <li>Identify which queries need indexes</li>
                    <li>Suggest query optimizations</li>
                    <li>Estimate execution time for large datasets</li>
                </ul>
                
                <b>Task 3: Security Audit</b>
                <ul>
                    <li>Identify potential SQL injection points</li>
                    <li>Suggest parameterized query implementations</li>
                    <li>Design an audit logging system</li>
                    <li>Create backup and recovery procedures</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h3>Key Learning Points for Day 2:</h3>

            <ol>
                <li><b>SELECT Mastery:</b> Retrieve exactly the data you need with filtering, sorting, and limiting</li>
                <li><b>INSERT Techniques:</b> Add data with proper validation and handling duplicates</li>
                <li><b>UPDATE Safety:</b> Modify data without accidentally affecting wrong records</li>
                <li><b>DELETE Caution:</b> Remove data safely with proper backup strategies</li>
                <li><b>WHERE Clause:</b> The most important part of UPDATE and DELETE operations</li>
                <li><b>Query Optimization:</b> Write efficient SQL that performs well with large datasets</li>
                <li><b>Data Integrity:</b> Maintain consistency across related tables</li>
                <li><b>Security Practices:</b> Protect against SQL injection and data loss</li>
            </ol>

            <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; margin: 20px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
                <h3>üí° SQL Writing Best Practices:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Use Uppercase Keywords:</b> SELECT, FROM, WHERE (easier to read)</li>
                    <li><b>Format for Readability:</b> Line breaks, indentation, consistency</li>
                    <li><b>Use Aliases:</b> Meaningful names for columns and tables</li>
