        <h3>Troubleshooting Common Issues</h3>

        <b>Solving phpMyAdmin Problems:</b>
        <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
        // 1. "Cannot log in to MySQL server" Error
        Possible causes:
        - Wrong username/password
        - MySQL service not running
        - Host restriction
        - Password expired

        Solutions:
        1. Check MySQL service: sudo systemctl status mysql
        2. Reset root password:
        sudo systemctl stop mysql
        sudo mysqld_safe --skip-grant-tables &
        mysql -u root
        FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
        ALTER USER 'root'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'newpassword';
        exit
        sudo systemctl start mysql

        // 2. "The mysqli extension is missing"
        Install PHP MySQL extension:
        sudo apt install php-mysql  # Ubuntu/Debian
        sudo yum install php-mysql  # CentOS/RHEL

        Enable in php.ini:
        extension=mysqli

        Restart web server:
        sudo systemctl restart apache2

        // 3. "Maximum execution time exceeded"
        Increase limits in php.ini:
        max_execution_time = 300
        max_input_time = 300
        memory_limit = 256M

        For specific script in .htaccess:
        php_value max_execution_time 300

        // 4. "File upload size too small"
        Increase in php.ini:
        upload_max_filesize = 100M
        post_max_size = 100M

        // 5. "Access denied for user" Error
        Check user privileges:
        SHOW GRANTS FOR 'username'@'localhost';

        Grant privileges:
        GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON database.* TO 'username'@'localhost';
        FLUSH PRIVILEGES;

        // 6. phpMyAdmin Blank/White Screen
        Enable error reporting in config:
        $cfg['SendErrorReports'] = 'always';

        Check PHP error log:
        tail -f /var/log/apache2/error.log

        Common fixes:
        - Clear browser cache
        - Check PHP version compatibility
        - Verify file permissions

        // 7. "Too many connections" Error
        Increase max_connections in my.cnf:
        [mysqld]
        max_connections = 200

        Check current connections:
        SHOW PROCESSLIST;

        Kill problematic connections:
        KILL [process_id];

        // 8. Import/Export File Size Issues
        For large files:
        1. Use command line (mysqldump/mysql)
        2. Split SQL file into chunks
        3. Increase PHP limits as above
        4. Use compression (gzip)

        Split SQL file:
        split -l 1000 largefile.sql part_

        // 9. Character Encoding Problems
        Set correct charset in config:
        $cfg['DefaultCharset'] = 'utf8mb4';
        $cfg['DefaultConnectionCollation'] = 'utf8mb4_unicode_ci';

        MySQL config:
        [mysqld]
        character-set-server=utf8mb4
        collation-server=utf8mb4_unicode_ci

        // 10. Performance Issues
        Optimizations:
        1. Enable query cache
        2. Add indexes on frequently searched columns
        3. Regular table optimization
        4. Monitor slow queries

        Enable slow query log:
        [mysqld]
        slow_query_log = 1
        slow_query_log_file = /var/log/mysql/slow.log
        long_query_time = 2
        </pre>
        </div>

