<div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; margin: 20px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
    <h3>üí° Database Connection Best Practices:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Use Prepared Statements:</b> Always! This prevents SQL injection attacks</li>
        <li><b>Store Credentials Securely:</b> Never hardcode credentials, use environment variables</li>
        <li><b>Implement Connection Pooling:</b> Reuse connections to reduce overhead</li>
        <li><b>Set Appropriate Timeouts:</b> Prevent long-running connections from consuming resources</li>
        <li><b>Use SSL/TLS:</b> Encrypt connections, especially in production</li>
        <li><b>Implement Retry Logic:</b> Handle temporary connection failures gracefully</li>
        <li><b>Monitor Connections:</b> Track connection counts, durations, and errors</li>
        <li><b>Close Connections:</b> Explicitly close connections when done (though PDO handles this)</li>
        <li><b>Use Persistent Connections Carefully:</b> They can cause issues in some environments</li>
        <li><b>Test Failover:</b> Ensure your application handles database failures gracefully</li>
        <li><b>Regularly Update:</b> Keep PHP and database drivers updated for security and performance</li>
        <li><b>Backup Configuration:</b> Regularly backup database configuration and credentials</li>
    </ul>
</div>

