    <h3>Hands-On Exercise: Complete Auth System</h3>
    
    <b>Task:</b> Build a complete authentication system with all security features<br/><br/>
    
    <b>Requirements:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>Core Features:</b><br/>
        1. User registration with email verification<br/>
        2. Secure login with remember me<br/>
        3. Password reset functionality<br/>
        4. Account management (change password, update profile)<br/>
        5. Admin panel for user management<br/>
        6. Logout on all devices<br/>
        <br/>
        <b>Security Features:</b><br/>
        1. Password hashing with bcrypt<br/>
        2. CSRF protection on all forms<br/>
        3. Brute force protection (5 attempts, 15-minute lock)<br/>
        4. HTTPS enforcement<br/>
        5. Secure cookies (HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite)<br/>
        6. Session hijacking prevention<br/>
        7. Input validation and sanitization<br/>
        8. Rate limiting on authentication endpoints<br/>
        <br/>
        <b>Database Features:</b><br/>
        1. Proper indexes on all lookup fields<br/>
        2. Foreign key constraints<br/>
        3. Cascading deletes<br/>
        4. Audit logging of all auth events<br/>
    </div>
    
