    <h3>In-Depth Explanation</h3>
    
    <b>a. Understanding FTP Protocols</b><br/>
    
    <b>FTP (File Transfer Protocol):</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <b>How FTP Works:</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Uses two channels: Command (port 21) and Data (port 20)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Active mode: Server connects back to client for data<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Passive mode: Client connects to server for data (better for firewalls)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Plain text transmission (not secure)<br/>
        <br/>
        <b>Ports Used:</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ FTP: Port 21 (command), 20 (data - active mode)<br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Random ports for passive mode data transfer<br/>
        <br/>
        <b>Security Issues:</b><br/>
        ‚Ä¢ Credentials sent in plain text<br/>
