                html: `<h1>Week 13, Day 4: SSL Certificates, HTTPS & Web Security Basics</h1>
    <p>Today we'll learn how to secure websites with SSL certificates, implement HTTPS, and understand essential web security practices to protect your applications and users.</p>
    
    <div class="analogy-box">
        <b>Analogy: Securing a Physical Store üîí</b><br/>
       HTTP vs HTTPS: Regular mail vs. Certified registered mail<br/>
       SSL Certificate: Business license displayed in your store window<br/>
       Encryption: Writing messages in a secret code only you and recipient can read<br/>
       Certificate Authority (CA): Government office that issues official licenses<br/>
       Public/Private Keys: A special mailbox with two slots - one for receiving (public), one for opening (private)<br/>
       Man-in-the-Middle Attack: Someone secretly reading your mail before it reaches the recipient<br/>
       Hashing: Creating a unique fingerprint of your data<br/>
       SQL Injection: Tricking a guard into letting you into a restricted area
    </div>

    <h3>Key Topics</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Understanding HTTP vs HTTPS</li>
