        <li>Common Web Security Threats</li>
        <li>Security Headers and Best Practices</li>
        <li>Implementing HTTPS on Your Server</li>
    </ul>

      <h3>In-Depth Explanation</h3>
    
    <b>a. HTTP vs HTTPS: The Foundation of Web Security</b><br/>
    
    <b>The Problem with HTTP:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            // HTTP Request (Plain Text - Like a Postcard)
            GET /login HTTP/1.1
            Host: example.com
            User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0
            Cookie: session_id=abc123
            Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
            
            username=admin&password=secret123
            
            // ‚ùå Problems:
            // 1. Anyone can read it (network admin, ISP, hackers)
            // 2. Can be modified in transit
            // 3. No way to verify server identity
            // 4. Vulnerable to session hijacking
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>HTTPS Solution:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            // HTTPS Request (Encrypted - Like a Sealed Envelope)
            TLS Handshake Happens First:
            1. Client: "Hello Server, I support TLS 1.3"
            2. Server: "Hello Client, here's my certificate"
            3. Client: "Verifies certificate with CA"
            4. Both: "Generate shared secret key"
            5. Client: "Encrypts data with shared key"
            
            Encrypted Data Sent:
            ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ
            ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ
            ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ
            
            // ‚úÖ Advantages:
            // 1. Encryption: Data is unreadable to outsiders
            // 2. Integrity: Data cannot be modified undetected
            // 3. Authentication: Verifies server identity
            // 4. Trust: Browser shows green padlock
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>Visual Difference in Browser:</b>
    <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 15px 0;">
        <tr style="background-color: #f0f0f0;">
