     <b>b. SSL/TLS Certificates: Digital Passports</b><br/>
    
    <b>What's in a Certificate?</b>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            // Certificate Contents (Like a Passport):
            {
              "version": "3",
              "serialNumber": "1234567890",
              "signatureAlgorithm": "SHA256-RSA",
              
              "issuer": { // Who issued it (CA)
                "country": "US",
                "organization": "Let's Encrypt",
                "commonName": "Let's Encrypt Authority X3"
              },
              
              "validity": { // Expiration dates
                "notBefore": "2024-01-01T00:00:00Z",
                "notAfter": "2024-04-01T00:00:00Z"
              },
              
              "subject": { // Who it's issued to
                "country": "CA",
                "state": "Ontario",
                "locality": "Toronto",
                "organization": "Example Corp",
                "commonName": "example.com",
                "subjectAltNames": ["www.example.com", "shop.example.com"]
