              "publicKey": "-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----...",
              "signature": "-----BEGIN SIGNATURE-----..." // CA's digital signature
            }
            
            // Certificate Verification Process:
            // 1. Browser receives certificate
            // 2. Checks if CA is trusted (built-in list)
            // 3. Verifies digital signature
            // 4. Checks expiration date
            // 5. Verifies domain matches
            // 6. Establishes encrypted connection
        </pre>
    </div>

       
    <b>Types of SSL Certificates:</b>
