 <b>d. Common Web Security Threats & Protection</b><br/>
    
    <b>1. SQL Injection (SQLi):</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            // ‚ùå VULNERABLE CODE
            $user_id = $_GET['id'];
            $query = "SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = $user_id";
            // Attacker sends: example.com/profile?id=1 OR 1=1
            // Becomes: SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = 1 OR 1=1
            // Returns ALL users!
            
            // ‚úÖ SECURE CODE (Using Prepared Statements)
            $stmt = $pdo->prepare("SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = :id");
            $stmt->execute(['id' => $user_id]);
            $user = $stmt->fetch();
            
            // Protection Methods:
            // 1. Use parameterized queries (PDO/mysqli prepared statements)
            // 2. Input validation and sanitization
            // 3. Use ORM (Object Relational Mapping)
            // 4. Least privilege database users
            // 5. Web Application Firewall (WAF)
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>2. Cross-Site Scripting (XSS):</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            // ‚ùå VULNERABLE CODE
            echo "&lt;div&gt;Hello " . $_GET['name'] . "!&lt;/div&gt;";
            // Attacker sends: ?name=&lt;script&gt;stealCookies()&lt;/script&gt;
            // Injects malicious JavaScript!
            
            // ‚úÖ SECURE CODE (Output Encoding)
            echo "&lt;div&gt;Hello " . htmlspecialchars($_GET['name'], ENT_QUOTES, 'UTF-8') . "!&lt;/div&gt;";
            // Becomes: &lt;div&gt;Hello &amp;lt;script&amp;gt;stealCookies()&amp;lt;/script&amp;gt;!&lt;/div&gt;
            
            // Protection Methods:
            // 1. Output encoding (htmlspecialchars, htmlentities)
            // 2. Content Security Policy (CSP) headers
            // 3. Input validation (allowlist approach)
            // 4. Use template engines with auto-escaping
            // 5. HttpOnly cookies for session management
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>3. Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF):</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            // ‚ùå VULNERABLE FORM
            &lt;form action="/transfer-money" method="POST"&gt;
                &lt;input type="hidden" name="amount" value="1000"&gt;
                &lt;input type="hidden" name="to_account" value="hacker123"&gt;
                &lt;button&gt;Win Free iPhone!&lt;/button&gt;
            &lt;/form&gt;
            // Hidden in attacker's site, auto-submits when user visits
            
            // ‚úÖ SECURE FORM (CSRF Tokens)
            session_start();
            $csrf_token = bin2hex(random_bytes(32));
            $_SESSION['csrf_token'] = $csrf_token;
            
            &lt;form action="/transfer-money" method="POST"&gt;
                &lt;input type="hidden" name="csrf_token" value="&lt;?= $csrf_token ?&gt;"&gt;
                &lt;input type="number" name="amount"&gt;
                &lt;input type="text" name="to_account"&gt;
                &lt;button&gt;Transfer&lt;/button&gt;
            &lt;/form&gt;
            
            // Server-side verification:
            if ($_POST['csrf_token'] !== $_SESSION['csrf_token']) {
                die("CSRF token validation failed!");
            }
            
            // Protection Methods:
            // 1. CSRF tokens (synchronizer token pattern)
            // 2. SameSite cookies
            // 3. Double submit cookies
            // 4. Custom headers for AJAX requests
            // 5. Require re-authentication for sensitive actions
        </pre>
    </div>
    
    <b>4. Session Hijacking:</b>
    <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <pre>
            // ‚ùå INSECURE SESSION CONFIGURATION
            ini_set('session.cookie_httponly', 0); // JavaScript can access
            ini_set('session.cookie_secure', 0);   // Works over HTTP
            ini_set('session.use_strict_mode', 0); // Accepts any session ID
            
            // ‚úÖ SECURE SESSION CONFIGURATION (php.ini or code)
            session_start([
                'cookie_lifetime' => 86400, // 24 hours
                'cookie_secure' => true,    // HTTPS only
                'cookie_httponly' => true,  // No JS access
                'cookie_samesite' => 'Strict', // CSRF protection
                'use_strict_mode' => true,  // Only accept valid session IDs
                'use_only_cookies' => true, // No session in URL
                'sid_length' => 128,        // Longer session IDs
                'sid_bits_per_character' => 6
            ]);
            
            // Regenerate session ID after login
            session_regenerate_id(true);
            
            // Additional protections:
            // 1. Bind sessions to IP address
            // 2. Set short session timeouts
            // 3. Logout functionality destroys session
            // 4. Monitor for multiple concurrent sessions
        </pre>
    </div>
    

